eden |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810075204/http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2009/11/26/westlife_in_sweden |url-status=dead |archive-date=2011-08-10 |title=Westlife in Sweden |publisher=westlife.com |date= |accessdate=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n*2019 Singapore, Indonesian, Chinese, Swedish Tour<ref name=\"Twitter\"/>\n\n==See also==\n{{Wikipedia books|Westlife}}\n*[[Boy band#Best-selling boy bands|List of best-selling boy bands]]\n*[[UK Singles Chart records and statistics]]\n* [[List of artists who reached number one on the UK Singles Chart]]\n* [[List of best-selling music artists in the United Kingdom in singles sales]]\n*[[List of artists by number of UK Singles Chart number ones]]\n*[[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 2000s]]\n*[[List of UK Singles Downloads Chart number ones of the 2000s]]\n*[[List of UK Albums Chart number ones of the 2000s]]\n* [[List of artists who reached number one in Ireland]]\n* [[List of songs that reached number one on the Irish Singles Chart]]\n*[[List of best-selling albums in the Philippines]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website|http://westlife.com}}\n\n{{Westlife}}\n{{Westlife songs}}\n{{Shane Filan}}\n{{Brian McFadden}}\n{{MTV EMA for Best UK & Ireland Act}}\n{{Portal bar|Music|1990s|Europe|Ireland}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Westlife| ]]\n[[Category:Brit Award winners]]\n[[Category:Irish boy bands]]\n[[Category:Irish pop music groups]]\n[[Category:1998 establishments in Ireland]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1998]]\n[[Category:Musical groups disestablished in 2012]]\n[[Category:Musical groups reestablished in 2018]]\n[[Category:2012 disestablishments in Ireland]]\n[[Category:2018 establishments in Ireland]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Dublin (city)]]\n[[Category:Ballad music groups]]\n[[Category:Teen pop groups]]\n[[Category:RCA Records artists]]\n[[Category:Sony BMG artists]]\n[[Category:Syco Music artists]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Group artists]]\n[[Category:Vocal quartets]]\n[[Category:Vocal quintets]]\n[[Category:World Music Awards winners]]\n[[Category:EMI Records artists]]\n[[Category:MTV EMA winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the band|their eponymous debut album|Westlife (album)}}\n{{short description|Irish pop group}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{POV|date=November 2019}}\n{{cleanup rewrite|date=November 2019}}\n{{cleanup-PR|date=November 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Westlife\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = Westlife 2011 3.jpg\n| landscape        = yes\n| caption          = Westlife performing live on their [[Gravity Tour]] in October 2011 in [[Hanoi]], Vietnam\n| origin           = [[Sligo]] and [[Dublin]], Ireland\n| genre            = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| years_active     = {{hlist|1998\u20132012|2018\u2013present}}\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Universal Music Group|Universal]]|[[Virgin EMI Records|Virgin EMI]]|[[EMI|EMI Australia]]|[[EMI Japan]] {{small|(current)}}|[[RCA Records|RCA]]|[[Syco Music|Syco]]|[[Sony Music|Sony]]|[[Sony BMG]]|[[S Records|S]]|[[Arista Records|Arista]]|[[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]] {{small|(Former)}}}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Steve Mac]]|[[Ed Sheeran]]|[[Mariah Carey]]|[[Diana Ross]]|[[Donna Summer]]|[[Delta Goodrem]]|[[Boyzone]]|[[Ronan Keating]]|[[Backstreet Boys]]|[[Cristian Castro]]|[[BoA]]|[[Lionel Richie]]}}\n| website          = {{URL|westlife.com}}\n| current_members  = * [[Shane Filan]]\n* [[Markus Feehily]]\n* [[Kian Egan]]\n* [[Nicky Byrne]]\n| past_members     = * [[Brian McFadden]]\n| module2          = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| channel_name = Westlife\n| channel_name2 = westlifeVEVO\n| years_active = 1999\u2013present\n| subscribers  = 2.6 million (combined)\n| views        = 1.6 billion (combined)\n| network      = ScaleLab<ref name=\"SocialBlade\">{{cite web|title=Westlife YouTube Stats, Channel Statistics|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/westlife|publisher=socialblade.com|accessdate=2 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Westlifevevo YouTube Stats, Channel Statistics|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/westlifevevo|publisher=socialblade.com|accessdate=8 October 2019}}</ref>\n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2012\n| gold_button     = yes\n| gold_year       = 2018\n| diamond_button  = no\n| ruby_button     = no\n| stats_update    = 11 November 2019\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Westlife''' are an Irish [[Pop music|pop]] vocal group, who were formed in 1998 in [[Sligo]], [[Ireland]]. They decided to go their seperate ways and disband in 2012, before getting back together in 2018. They were originally signed by [[Simon Cowell]] in the UK, [[Clive Davis]] in the US and managed by [[Louis Walsh]] and Sonny Takhar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irishmirror.ie/showbiz/irish-showbiz/westlife-reunion-croke-park-2019-13311082|title=Westlife set for major comeback at Croke Park in summer 2019|first=Connell|last=McHugh|date=26 September 2018|work=Irish Mirror}}</ref> The group currently consists of [[Shane Filan]], [[Markus Feehily|Mark Feehily]], [[Kian Egan]], and [[Nicky Byrne]], with [[Brian McFadden]] having left in 2004 to pursue a solo career. \n\nSo far, they have a total of thirteen major album releases, eleven of which are studio albums. Five albums are as a five-piece and eight are as a four-piece. The group rose to fame with their debut international self-titled studio album, ''[[Westlife (album)|Westlife]]'' (1999). It was followed by ''[[Coast to Coast (Westlife album)|Coast to Coast]]'' (2000), ''[[World of Our Own]]'' (2001), ''[[Unbreakable \u2013 The Greatest Hits Vol. 1]]'' (2002), and ''[[Turnaround (Westlife album)|Turnaround]]'' (2003), which continued the group's success worldwide. Before the start of their [[Turnaround Tour]] in 2004, one of the original members, [[Brian McFadden]], departed from the band. The four remaining members continued as a group to release their cover albums ''[[Allow Us to Be Frank]]'' (2004) and ''[[The Love Album (Westlife album)|The Love Album]]'' (2006) and the studio albums ''[[Face to Face (Westlife album)|Face to Face]]'' (2005) and ''[[Back Home (Westlife album)|Back Home]]'' (2007). After an almost one-year hiatus of studio recording in 2008, they regrouped and released the studio albums ''[[Where We Are]]'' (2009), and ''[[Gravity (Westlife album)|Gravity]]'' (2010), and the compilation album ''[[Greatest Hits (Westlife album)|Greatest Hits]]'' (2011). After eight years, the quartet group released their eleventh studio album, ''[[Spectrum (Westlife album)|Spectrum]]'', in 2019.\n\nThe band has sold over 45 million records.<ref>{{cite news  | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/1gTKw4XNh4jNKjFPvpC2Py1/nicky-byrne |title=BBC One - Strictly Come Dancing Profile|work= BBC |accessdate=January 18, 2019 |date=June 8, 2018}}</ref> The band has received over 1.5 billion views on their official [[YouTube]] channel alone with more than 2.4 million page subscribers as well,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x-QF3bdTwb8|title=SHANE FILAN \u2013 HEAVEN \u2013 Spekta Show Top 7 \u2013 Indonesian Idol 2018|last=Indonesian Idol|date=5 March 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref> were streamed more than 300 million times,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/ireland/irish-daily-mail/20180928/282106342570217|title=PressReader.com \u2013 Connecting People Through News|website=Pressreader.com}}</ref> and more than 550 million streams on [[Spotify]] as of 2018 and more than a million followers on the said streaming media platform as of May 2019.\n\nThey generated singles such as \"[[Swear It Again]]\", \"[[If I Let You Go]]\", \"[[Flying Without Wings]]\", \"[[I Have a Dream (song)|I Have a Dream]]\", \"[[Seasons in the Sun]]\", \"[[Fool Again]]\", \"[[My Love (Westlife song)|My Love]]\", \"[[What Makes a Man]]\", \"[[Uptown Girl]]\", \"[[Unbreakable (Westlife song)|Unbreakable]]\", \"[[When You're Looking Like That]]\", \"[[Queen of My Heart]]\", \"[[Mandy (Westlife song)|Mandy]]\", \"[[Tonight (Westlife song)|Tonight]]\", \"[[Hey Whatever]]\", \"[[You Raise Me Up]]\", \"[[Bop Bop Baby]]\", \"[[The Rose (song)|The Rose]]\", and \"[[World of Our Own]]\". 19 out their 29 singles as lead artist and as featured artist received UK certifications from 1999 to 2019, 17 out of 29 singles from 1999 to 2009 reached the top 2 on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. They have the second most certifications for a boy band in the UK Singles Chart after [[Take That]] and the most singles certifications for a pop band on the [[List of artists by number of UK Singles Chart number ones|UK number one singles artists chart]] since [[The Beatles]].\n\nAccording to the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI), Westlife has been certified for 13.1 million albums, 1.3 million video albums, and 10&nbsp;million singles, with a total of more than 24 million combined sales in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpi.co.uk/certified-awards.aspx |title=Certified Awards |publisher=Bpi.co.uk |date= |accessdate=4 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-official-top-20-biggest-selling-groups-of-all-time-revealed-1682/ |title=The Official Top 20 biggest selling groups of all time revealed! |publisher=Officialcharts.com |accessdate=6 April 2014}}</ref> They are also currently ranked 19th with the most number-one albums of all time and sixth highest band in the list.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/acts-with-the-most-number-1-albums-on-the-official-uk-chart__15643/ |title=Acts with the most Number 1 albums on the Official UK Chart |date=9 November 2018 |first=Justin |last=Myers |work=[[Official Charts Company]] |accessdate=31 January 2019}}</ref> The group have accumulated 14 number-one singles as a lead artist as well as having eight number-one albums in the United Kingdom, making them Ireland's most prolific chart-toppers. In 2012, the [[Official Charts Company]] listed Westlife 34th amongst the biggest-selling singles artist, 16th amongst the biggest selling groups, and 14th with most top ten hits all the highest for a boy band and a pop group in [[British pop music|British music]] history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-official-singles-charts-biggest-selling-artists-of-all-time-revealed-1431/ |title=Official Singles Charts' biggest selling artists of all time revealed |publisher=Officialcharts.com |accessdate=6 April 2014}}</ref> They are the biggest selling album group of the 2000s decade in the UK as well. Three of their studio albums were part of the 50 fastest selling albums of all time in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/photos/50-fastest-selling-albums-ever-1415019|title=50 fastest selling albums ever \u2013 NME|date=27 April 2011}}</ref> The group have the most consecutive number-one studio albums in a decade in the UK and Ireland for a band since the Beatles and for a pop band and act since [[ABBA]]. Also in Ireland, they have 11 number-one albums with a total of 13 top two albums, 16 number-one singles as well as 34 top-fifty singles.\n\nThey are holders of the following ''[[Guinness World Records]]'': first to achieve seven consecutive number-one singles in the UK, most public appearances in 36 hours by a pop group, most singles to debut at number one on the UK chart and top selling album group in the United Kingdom in the 21st century.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gettyimages.co.uk/detail/news-photo/westlife-with-pop-stars-the-rivals-girls-westlife-news-photo/104166692#/westlife-with-pop-stars-the-rivals-girls-westlife-celebrated-their-picture-id104166692 |title=Westlife Party |last=Benett |first=Dave |publisher=Getty Images UK}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/entertainment/uk-irish-embassy-honours-westlife-123103.html|title=UK Irish Embassy honours Westlife|work=Irish Examiner|date=26 November 2003}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/top-selling-album-act-of-the-21st-century-in-the-uk/|title=Top-selling album act of the 21st century in the UK|website=Guinness World Records}}</ref>\n\nIt makes Westlife one of the most successful musical groups of all time, among the highest profile acts in 2000s popular culture in most territories worldwide, and one of the few boy bands to have continued success after their commercial peak. On the [[Boy band|best-selling boy bands of all time]] list, they are currently eighth worldwide along with the biggest selling boy band from Ireland in history globally.\n\nWestlife have not managed to break into the US market so far, achieving only one hit single in 2000, \"Swear It Again\". Despite this, the United States ranked in the top five for the number of views of the band with an annual total of more than 30 million on their official [[YouTube]] channel alone with multiple videos uploaded as of June 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://charts.youtube.com/|title=YouTube Music Charts|website=charts.youtube.com}}</ref>\n\nThe pop band has received numerous [[List of awards and nominations received by Westlife|accolades]] including one [[World Music Award]], two [[Brit Awards]], four [[MTV Awards]], four [[The Record of the Year|Record of the Year Awards]], with an overall total of 91 awards and 20 nominations so far. As a live act, Westlife have sold 5.5&nbsp;million concert tickets worldwide from their fourteen concert tours so far. They still hold the record for the most shows played at [[Odyssey Complex|The SSE Arena]], [[Belfast]] and [[The SSE Arena, Wembley|SSE Arena]], [[Wembley]]. It makes them the biggest arena act of all-time in the United Kingdom. They sold out [[Croke Park]] Stadium in their home country in a record-breaking five minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/westlife/about?disable_polymer=1|title=Westlife \u2013 About|date=25 September 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref> Their fourteenth, and latest concert tour is called [[Stadiums in the Summer Tour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.simonjonespr.com/news/2018/10/17/westlife-announce-the-twenty-tour|title=Westlife Announce 'The Twenty Tour' |website=simonjonespr.com |accessdate=2018-10-18}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===Origin: Byrne, Egan, Feehily, Filan, and McFadden's beginnings===\n[[Kian Egan]], [[Mark Feehily]] and [[Shane Filan]] were schoolmates in [[Summerhill College]] in [[Sligo]], Ireland. All three of them participated in a school production of ''[[Grease (musical)|Grease]]'' with fellow Sligo men Derrick Lacey, Graham Keighron, and Michael Garrett. They considered it as the start of Westlife. The six mentioned individuals formed a pop vocal group called '''Six as One''' in 1997. They changed their band name to '''IOYOU''' later. Before this, Egan was part of a [[punk-rock]] band called '''Skrod'''. The group, managed by choreographer Mary McDonagh and two other informal managers, released a single titled \"[[Together Girl Forever]]\" under Sound Records which was written by Feehily and Filan with fellow Irish [[Those Nervous Animals]] and The Strong are Lonely band members Padraig Meehan and Daragh Connolly. Another song \"Everlasting Love\" included in the single was written by Feehily, Keighron, Meehan, and Connolly. There is also an unreleased song called \"Good Thing\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1626452.stm|title=Westlife manager tells it straight|date=29 October 2001|via=news.bbc.co.uk}}</ref> McDonagh first encountered Egan as a six-year-old student at her weekly dance classes, and came to know Filan and Feehily in their early teens as they starred in shows such as ''[[Oliver!]]'' and ''[[Godspell]]'' for Sligo Fun Company.\n[[File:Louis Walsh2009July.jpg|thumb|100px|right|Westlife is managed by [[Louis Walsh]].]][[File:Simon Cowell in December 2011.jpg|thumb|100px|right|Westlife was originally signed by [[Simon Cowell]].]]\n[[Louis Walsh]], the manager of fellow Irish boy band [[Boyzone]], came to know the group after he was contacted by Filan's mother, Mae Filan, but the group failed to secure a [[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]] record deal with Simon Cowell. Cowell told Walsh: \"You are going to have to fire at least three of them. They have great voices, but they are the ugliest band I have ever seen in my life.\"<ref>{{cite book |last= Cowell |first= Simon |title= I Don't Mean to Be Rude, But... |publisher= Broadway Books |year= 2003 |isbn= 0-7679-1741-3 |url-access= registration |url= https://archive.org/details/idontmeantoberud00cowe }}</ref> Three members of the band (Lacey, Keighron, and Garrett) were told they would not be part of the new group, and auditions were held in Dublin where [[Nicky Byrne]] and [[Brian McFadden]] were recruited. McFadden was part of an [[R&B]] group called '''Cartel''' before this.\n\nThe new group, formed on 3 July 1998, was renamed '''Westside''' but that name was already in use by another band, so it was changed to Westlife. It was revealed that Walsh was already calling them Westlife before Westside name came along.<ref name=\"Bower 2012\">{{cite book |last= Bower |first= Tom |title= Sweet Revenge: The Intimate Life of Simon Cowell |publisher=Random House Publishing Group |year= 2012 |isbn= 978-0345533951 }}</ref> In ''[[Westlife \u2013 Our Story]]'', Byrne revealed that, unlike the others in the group, he was keen to change the name to West High. McFadden also changed the spelling of his name to Bryan to make it easier to sign autographs. They managed to secure a major record deal the second time around under BMG with all other record labels competed. They have signed a four million pound record deal with [[RCA Records]]. Westlife's first big break came in 1998 when they opened for Boyzone and [[Backstreet Boys]]' concerts in Dublin. Boyzone singer [[Ronan Keating]] was brought in to co-manage the group with Walsh. Later, they won a special Smash Hits Roadshow award at that year's ''[[Smash Hits Poll Winners Party]]''. Their first live television performance as a group in Ireland and worldwide was on the Irish TV series and the world's second longest-running late-night talk show, ''[[The Late Late Show (Irish TV series)|The Late Late Show]]'' that had its broadcast on 13 November 1998. They performed \"[[Flying Without Wings]]\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rte.ie/archives/2018/1108/1009544-when-westlife-were-westside/ |title=Welcome Westside 1998 |publisher=RTE}}</ref> The band then released an [[Extended play|EP]] titled ''[[Swear It Again]]'' afterwards. Both recorded songs under Westside were produced by [[Steve Mac]] and written by Mac and [[Wayne Hector]]. The debut extended play and single was chosen by Cowell with the guidance of his father, [[Eric Cowell]]. His father stated then, \"I think they will be big\".<ref name=\"Bower 2012\"/>\n\n===International breakthrough, Debut album, ''Coast to Coast, World of Our Own'' and super stardom (1999\u20132002)===\n[[File:Shane Filan Right Here album.png|thumb|200px|upright|left|Most appeared Irish act and Irish male act in the [[UK Singles Chart|UK number one singles chart]], Shane Steven Filan]][[File:Markus Feehily 2015.tiff|thumb|200px|upright|left|Most appeared [[LGBT]] member and Irish LGBT personality in the [[UK Singles Chart|UK number one singles chart]], Markus Michael Patrick Feehily]]{{multiple image\n| align = left\n| image1 = Kian_Egan_2011.jpg\n| width1 = 185\n| alt1 = \n| caption1 = \n| image2 = ESC2016_-_Ireland_01_10.jpg\n| width2 = 160\n| alt2 = \n| caption2 = \n| footer = Kian John Francis Kelly Egan ''(left)'' and Nicholas Bernard James Adam McGarry Byrne, Jr. ''(right)'' are two of the original members of Westlife.\n}}\nIn April 1999, the group released their first single, \"Swear It Again\" which immediately topped the charts in Ireland and in the UK for two weeks. It became the biggest-selling single in a week one by a debut artist.<ref name=\"billboard clive davis westlife\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/?id=1A0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA110&lpg=PA110&dq=billboard+clive+davis+westlife#v=onepage&q=billboard+clive+davis+westlife&f=false|title=Dublin Darling Westlife Wins Over Europe, Aims For Success in U.S. |work=Billboard|first=Nielsen Business Media|last=Inc|date=5 February 2000|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref name=\"GMTV\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gm.tv/index.cfm?articleid=27201%20Westlife%20announcement|title=Westlife on GMTV|publisher=[[GMTV]]|accessdate=22 December 2007|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071227072311/http://www.gm.tv/index.cfm?articleid=27201%20Westlife%20announcement|archivedate=27 December 2007}}</ref> On the week of its release and its chart achievement announcement, Cowell's father died. Their second single, \"[[If I Let You Go]]\" was released in August 1999, which established them as the first boy band to hit the No. 1 with its first two singles.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/?id=1A0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA110&lpg=PA110&dq=billboard+clive+davis+westlife#v=onepage&q=billboard+clive+davis+westlife&f=false|title=Found the 'Love' of a Westlife Time |work=Billboard|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc|date=5 February 2000|via=Google Books}}</ref> They also performed for billions in 1999 at the [[Miss World]] telecast with this song. The third single was the highly acclaimed \"Flying Without Wings\" (their first '[[The Record of the Year|Record of the Year]]' and their third No. 1 single), released in October the same year, also followed suit. It made them the only the second Irish act and fourth act to debut at No. 1 with their first three singles, [[B*Witched]], [[Robson and Jerome]], and [[Spice Girls]] being the other three. \"Flying Without Wings\" was also included on the soundtrack of the [[Warner Brothers]] film, ''[[Pok\u00e9mon: The Movie 2000]]''. Their first album, simply titled ''[[Westlife (album)|Westlife]]'', was released in November 1999 and went to No. 2 in the UK and their first No. 1 in Ireland. The album was the biggest chart dropper on the top 40 in UK music history when, in its 58th week on the charts it leapt from No. 79 to No. 3 before falling to No. 37 the following week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.everyhit.com/recordalb.html|title=Record-Breakers and Trivia \u2013 Albums |website=everyhit.com}}</ref> Despite the history, the album successfully managed to peak at No. 1 in [[Scotland]] in the year 2001 after premiering at No. 6 at the [[Scottish Albums Chart]] in 1999.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/scottish-albums-chart/20010114/40/|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=17 February 2013|title=Scottish Albums (14 January 2001)}}</ref>\n\nIn December 1999, a fourth and a double-side single was released, \"[[I Have A Dream (ABBA song)#Westlife version|I Have A Dream]]\"/\"[[Seasons in the Sun#Westlife version|Seasons in the Sun]]\". It knocked [[Cliff Richard]]'s \"[[The Millennium Prayer]]\" off the top spot and earned them the 1999 UK [[Christmas number-one single]]. It is also their fourth No. 1 single.<ref name=BB2>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=949719|title=Westlife, Shania Top UK. Christmas Charts|work=Billboard|date=20 December 1999|accessdate=22 December 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=869373|title=Westlife Tops UK Singles Chart For 4th Week|last=Sexton|first=Paul|work=Billboard|date=10 January 2000|accessdate=22 December 2007}}</ref> It was the first official No. 1 single music act in the [[2000s decade]] of [[UK Singles Chart]] and also the last official No. 1 single music act in the [[1990s]] decade of UK Singles Chart. They are also the only music act to have four number ones in UK Singles Chart in only a year. The fifth and last single from the album, \"[[Fool Again]]\", also peaked at No. 1.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=867023|title=Westlife Go Five For Five on UK Singles Chart|last=Sexton|first=Paul|work=Billboard|date=3 April 2000|accessdate=22 December 2007}}</ref> With this, they broke records of being the only male band to have every singles released from an album to reach No. 1 in the UK and the only male group with most original songs in an album that went straight to No. 1 in the UK with multiple and/or with four original singles. Afterwards, Westlife signed to [[Arista Records]] for the [[North America]]n territory after auditioning for the label's founder, Clive Davis.<ref name=\"Taylor\">{{cite journal|first=Chuck|last=Taylor|date=5 February 2000|title=Dublin's Darling Westlife Wins Over Europe, Aims For Success in U.S.|journal=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Nielsen Company|Nielsen Business Media]]|volume=112|issue=6|page=110|issn=0006-2510}}</ref> Then the group had a promotional tour in the United States for their \"Swear It Again\" single and peaked at No. 20 in the [[Billboard Hot 100]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allbusiness.com/retail-trade/miscellaneous-retail-retail-stores-not/4636231-1.html |title=Radio Concert Monitor &#124; Professional Journal archives from |publisher=AllBusiness.com |accessdate=13 October 2011}}</ref> An [[Asia]]n tour followed in support of their debut album before releasing a second album. On 1 July 2000, they were honored as Freemen of the Borough of Sligo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/archives/2015/0701/711877-westlife-freemen-of-sligo/ |title=Westlife Honoured with Freedom of Sligo 2000 |website=rte.ie}}</ref>\n\n''[[Coast to Coast (Westlife album)|Coast to Coast]]'', their second album, was released a year later and was their first No.&nbsp;1 UK album, beating the Spice Girls' ''[[Forever (Spice Girls album)|Forever]]'' album by a large margin, the said chart battle was widely reported by [[Media of the United Kingdom|British media]]. It became the country's 4th biggest selling album of 2000.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=875951\n |title =Westlife Outlasts Spice Girls in UK Chart War\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]]\n |date =13 November 2000\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n }}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://bpi.co.uk/platinum/platinumright.asp?rq=search_plat&r_id=29350\n |title=Platinum Awards\n |publisher=[[British Phonographic Industry]]\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071227144148/http://bpi.co.uk/platinum/platinumright.asp?rq=search_plat&r_id=29350\n |archivedate=27 December 2007\n |url-status=dead\n\n}}</ref> This is their second No. 1 album in Ireland. The album was preceded by a duet with [[Mariah Carey]] singing \"[[Against All Odds (Take a Look at Me Now)#Westlife and Mariah Carey version|Against All Odds (Take a Look at Me Now)]]\" and the original song \"[[My Love (Westlife song)|My Love]]\" (their second Record of the Year award). Both singles reached No.&nbsp;1 on the UK charts, their sixth and seventh number ones respectively.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=876235\n |title =Westlife Defy The 'Odds' On UK Singles Chart\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]]\n |date =25 September 2000\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=875991\n |title =Westlife Continues UK Singles Chart Monopoly\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]]\n |date =6 November 2000\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> With this, Westlife broke an unexpected record of the most consecutive No. 1 singles in the UK, having their first seven consecutive singles debut at the top by a debuting act and group, and by an act, a group, a male group, a pop act and a pop group in UK and became the fastest number one music act beating [[Elvis Presley]]'s previous record of three years versus 23 months of Westlife getting each its first No. 1 singles and second music act to have the longest string of number ones in UK history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/?id=0BAEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA124&lpg=PA124&dq=billboard+books+westlife#v=onepage&q=billboard+books+westlife&f=false|title=<!--ACTUAL ARTICLE TITLE BELONGS HERE!--> |work=Billboard|first=Nielsen Business Media|last=Inc|date=18 November 2000|via=Google Books}}</ref> However, in December 2000, their eighth and an Ireland and UK exclusive single \"[[What Makes a Man]]\", only debuted at No. 2.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=874898\n |title =Bob The Builder Ends Westlife's UK Chart Run\n |publisher=Billboard charts |date=26 December 2000\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071227121250/http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=874898\n |archivedate=27 December 2007 }}</ref> The single \"My Love\" was controversially used by [[Central Intelligence Agency]] as part of a torture program in [[Afghanistan]]. According to the [[American Civil Liberties Union]], \"the music pounded constantly as part of a scheme to assault prisoners\u2019 senses\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aclu.org/issues/national-security/torture/out-darkness|title=Out of the Darkness|website=American Civil Liberties Union}}</ref> They survived the 2000 [[Mexico City]] major earthquake and lightning during this time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbiz.ie/news/august00/16-westlife08.shtml|title=ShowBiz Ireland \u2013 Westlife survive earthquake in Mexico|first=Raymond|last=Senior|website=showbiz.ie}}</ref> Outside the UK and Ireland, they gained chart success with \"[[I Lay My Love on You]]\" and \"[[When You're Looking Like That]]\". This time as well, they were included in the top ten earners list of all acts in UK and Ireland and sold over 2.5&nbsp;million units in [[Asia Pacific region]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=WCQxDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT107&lpg=PT107&dq=ifpi+statistics+WESTLIFE#v=onepage&q=ifpi%20statistics%20WESTLIFE&f=false|title=The Irishness of Irish Music|isbn=9781351543361|last1=O'Flynn|first1=John|date=5 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/?id=hRIEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA38-IA8&lpg=PA38-IA8&dq=WESTLIFE+SOLD#v=onepage&q=WESTLIFE%20SOLD&f=false|title=Billboard 11 Aug 2001|date=11 August 2001}}</ref> Also in this year, they launched their first world tour, \"[[Where Dreams Come True Tour]]\".<ref name=GMTV/> A recording of a concert from the tour live from Dublin was released in 19 November 2001. Also in the same month and year, Westlife released their third album ''[[World of Our Own]]'', their second No. 1 album in the UK and their third No. 1 album in Ireland.\n\n\"[[Uptown Girl#Westlife version|Uptown Girl]]\", \"[[Queen of My Heart]]\" and \"[[World of Our Own (song)|World of Our Own]]\" were released as singles, all of which peaked at No.&nbsp;1 in the UK. Those singles are also their eighth, ninth, and tenth number ones respectively.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/77328/westlife-return-to-form-on-uk-singles-chart\n |title =Westlife Return To Form on UK Singles Chart\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] | first=Paul | last=Sexton\n |date=12 March 2001 | accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/77770/westlife-steps-top-uk-charts\n |title =Westlife, Steps Top UK Charts\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] | first=Paul | last=Sexton\n |date=12 November 2001 | accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/77696/boy-bands-crowd-uk-charts\n |title =Boy Bands Crowd UK Charts\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] | first=Paul | last=Sexton\n |date =19 November 2001 | accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> With their tenth No. 1, they made history by being the shortest music act or band to have ten or double-figures number ones in the UK Singles Chart (2 years and 10 months or 149 weeks) \u2013 more than 3 months quicker than [[The Beatles]] (165 weeks). \"[[Bop Bop Baby]]\" was also released as a single, but it peaked at No.&nbsp;5 in the UK. In 2002, Westlife went on their second world tour, the [[World of Our Own Tour]] (In The Round). Overall in 2002, [[Irish Recorded Music Association|IRMA]] awarded the band plaque about their 1 million units sold in Ireland and ranked seventh as Irish's millionaires under age 30 with 18&nbsp;million euros for all the five members.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whytes.ie/art/westlife-1000000-sales-award/147360/?SearchString=&LotNumSearch=&GuidePrice=&OrderBy=LH&ArtistID=&ArrangeBy=list&NumPerPage=1000&offset=400 |title=Westlife, 1,000,000 sales award |publisher=whytes.ie}}</ref> For every performance each band member will get 228,000 euros, which means the 68 dates raked in 1.55&nbsp;million [[euros]] for them by June 2002. The cash rolled in from sales of their merchandise, while a recent advertising deal with [[Adidas]] was worth 488,000 euros to each of them with a total of 3.33&nbsp;million euros each at the end of the said tour.<ref name=GMTV/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefreelibrary.com/Westlife+of+luxury;+POP+STARS+ARE+NO7+ON+YOUNG+RICH+LIST.-a084515449|title=Westlife of luxury; POP STARS ARE NO7 ON YOUNG RICH LIST. \u2013 Free Online Library|website=thefreelibrary.com}}</ref>\n\n===''Unbreakable'', ''Turnaround'', and departure of Brian (2002\u20132004)===\n[[File:Brianmcfadden.jpg|thumb|upright|100px|right|[[Brian McFadden]] left Westlife for his family and later released his solo music.]]\nThe group sold more than 12 million records in a span of three years during this time.<ref>{{cite news\n |url =https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2002/11/17/184268/unbreakable-fitting-title-westlife\n |title =Unbreakable: A fitting title for the Westlife |newspaper=[[Philippine Star]] |first =Jonathan |last =Chua |date =17 November 2002\n |accessdate=22 December 2007 }}</ref> They released their eleventh UK No.&nbsp;1 single, \"[[Unbreakable (Westlife song)|Unbreakable]]\" in 2002.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/73509/westlife-blue-top-uk-charts\n |title =Westlife, Blue Top UK Charts |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] |first =Paul |last =Sexton |date =11 November 2002\n |accessdate=22 December 2007 }}</ref> Amidst rumours of a split, Westlife released their first greatest hits album in November that same year titled ''[[Unbreakable - The Greatest Hits Vol. 1]]'', which zoomed all the way to No.&nbsp;1 in the UK and Ireland. Their third No. 1 in the UK and the fourth one in Ireland. Also during that time, Westlife bagged another ''Guinness World Record'' for most public appearances by a pop group in a 36-hour period. The band made stop-offs in five different cities (Dublin, [[Belfast]], [[Edinburgh]], [[London]] and [[Manchester]]) to promote their then-new album. The release was followed by the double A-side single \"[[Tonight (Westlife song)|Tonight]]\"/\"[[Miss You Nights]]\", which debuted at No.&nbsp;3 in the UK and No. 1 in Ireland.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/71757/linkin-park-room-5-crash-into-uk-charts\n |title =Linkin Park, Room 5 Crash into UK Charts |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] |first =Paul |last =Sexton |date =31 March 2003 |accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> At this time, Because Films Inspire made a TV documentary titled \"Wild Westlife\", directed by Iain MacDonald and starred the group, featuring their daily life as musicians and their tour experiences. It was aired on [[BBC Choice]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/737025 |title=BFI &#124; Film & TV Database &#124; WILD WESTLIFE (2002) |publisher=Ftvdb.bfi.org.uk |date=16 April 2009 |accessdate=13 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120124102557/http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/737025 |archive-date=24 January 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2003, Westlife went on their third world tour, [[Greatest Hits Tour (Westlife)|The Greatest Hits Tour]] and invited to play at the annual [[Edinburgh Military Tattoo]], shrugging off rumours of a split which is what most of the pop bands do after a Greatest Hits album and tour.<ref>{{cite web |url =https://movies.yahoo.com/movie/1808641051/info |title =Westlife: The Greatest Hits Tour (2003) |publisher=[[Yahoo]] Music |accessdate=22 December 2007 }}</ref> A recording of a concert from the tour, live from Manchester, was released in November 2003.\n\nBack in September 2003, Westlife released \"[[Hey Whatever]]\", which peaked at No.&nbsp;4 in the UK.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/68987/darkness-black-eyed-peas-lead-uk-charts\n |title =Darkness, Black Eyed Peas Lead UK Charts |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] |first =Paul |last =Sexton |date =22 September 2003 |accessdate=22 December 2007 }}</ref> Their fourth studio album, ''[[Turnaround (Westlife album)|Turnaround]]'', was then released in November, earning the group another UK No.&nbsp;1 album, the fourth one. The album is also their fifth No. 1 in Ireland. \"[[Mandy (Westlife Version)|Mandy]]\", was released a week before the album release. The band's twelfth No. 1 single. Their version won them their third Record of the Year award, in under five years.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/67971/young-westlife-top-uk-charts\n |title =Young, Westlife Top UK Charts |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] |first =Paul |last =Sexton |date =1 December 2003\n |accessdate=22 December 2007 }}</ref> Their version of \"Mandy\" is also considered the single with the longest leap to the top (from No.&nbsp;200 to No. 1) in UK music history.<ref name=eh>{{cite web |url =http://www.everyhit.com/record5.html |title =Record Breakers and Trivia: Singles: Individual Hits: Number 1s |publisher=EveryHit |accessdate=21 March 2008\n }}</ref> \"[[Obvious (Westlife song)|Obvious]]\" was released as the final single from the album, charting at No. 3.\n\nOn 9 March 2004, just three weeks prior to embarking on their fourth world tour, McFadden left the group to spend more time with his family and six months later to release solo music projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/westlife-18-1365525|title=WESTLIFE SPLIT \u2013 OFFICIAL \u2013 NME|date=9 March 2004}}</ref> On that day, a press conference was held where all the group's members were present, each giving emotional individual speeches. McFadden's final public performance as part of Westlife was at [[Newcastle upon Tyne]]'s Powerhouse nightclub on 27 February 2004.<ref>{{cite news\n |url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/music/3545399.stm\n |title =Boy-band Westlife become foursome\n |work=BBC News| date=9 March 2004 | accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url =https://www.amazon.co.uk/Westlife-Greatest-Hits-Tour/dp/B00009PACW/ref=pd_sxp_grid_pt_0_0\n |title =Westlife \u2013 Greatest Hits Tour [2004]\n | accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> McFadden attended the first day of the band's tour date as an audience. The last time the five had reunited in public was when McFadden acted in an Irish reality television show [[Anonymous (TV series)|Anonymous]] where he disguised as a fan in an album signing event of the group in November 2005 and had a broadcast in January 2006. He subsequently began a solo career, and reverted the spelling of his first name back to its original 'Brian'. McFadden later released more albums and singles, but only with moderate success.\n\nLess than a month after McFadden's departure, the group kicked off their \"Turnaround Tour\".<ref name=\"billboard.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/1325402/study-uk-arena-attendance-ticket-sales-up|title=Study: U.K. Arena Attendance, Ticket Sales Up|website=Billboard}}</ref> A live version of \"[[Flying Without Wings]]\" from the said tour was released as an official UK download, earning them the first official UK Downloads No. 1.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3617020.stm|title=Westlife top first download chart|date=1 September 2004|publisher=BBC}}</ref> A recording of a concert from the Turnaround Tour, live from [[Stockholm, Sweden]], was released in November 2003.\n\n===''Face to Face'', ''Back Home'', and cover albums (2004\u20132008)===\nIn September 2004, they performed on the [[World Music Awards]], where they were recognised as the Best Irish Act of that year. They then released a [[Rat Pack]]-inspired album and fifth album ''...[[Allow Us to Be Frank]]'', which peaked at No. 3. No singles from this album were released in the UK but \"[[Ain't That a Kick in the Head?]]\", accompanied with a music video, was released as a digital download in the UK and peaked at No. 4 and as a physical single in other [[Europe]]an countries. \"[[Smile (Charlie Chaplin song)|Smile]]\" and \"[[Fly Me to the Moon]]\", both with music videos as well, were released as digital downloads only.\n\nPrior to the release of the ''...Allow Us to Be Frank'' album, Westlife scouted for \"the perfect fan\" to help promote their album.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/800132 |title=Westlife She's the One (2004) |work=BFI |date=16 April 2009 |accessdate=13 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222085206/http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/800132 |archive-date=22 February 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> After ''[[The X Factor (TV series)|X Factor]]''-style auditions, they found Joanne Hindley, who recorded \"[[The Way You Look Tonight]]\" with the group.<ref name=\"GMTV\" /> To mark this special collaboration, a special programme was televised, showing auditions and live performances, called ''She's The One'', presented by [[Kate Thornton]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/4ce2b8ada5104|title=Westlife She&#039;s the One (2004)|website=BFI}}</ref> It also featured a live performance by their fathers with their version of \"[[That's Life (song)|That's Life]]\". Westlife continued to tour Europe as part of their \"[[The Number Ones Tour]]\" which started in early 2005. The tour at ranked at number 84 worldwide with top concert tour ticket sales with 191,361.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pollstarpro.com/specialfeatures2005/2005YearendTop100WorldWideTours.pdf|title=Pollstar \u2013 Welcome to the New Pollstar!|website=pollstarpro.com|access-date=23 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161008122240/http://www.pollstarpro.com/specialfeatures2005/2005YearendTop100WorldWideTours.pdf|archive-date=8 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> A recording of a concert from the tour, live from [[Sheffield]], was released in November 2005.\n\nBy 2004, they sold over 30 million albums already, the biggest live act in UK, and making around \u00a34m each as reported in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/westlife-im-with-the-brand-551646.html|title=Westlife: I'm with the brand|website=independent.co.uk}}</ref> In October 2005, Westlife returned with their comeback single, \"[[You Raise Me Up]]\", which was taken from their sixth album ''[[Face to Face (Westlife album)|Face to Face]]'', their thirteenth No. 1. On 5 November 2005, both the album and the single were at No.&nbsp;1 in the UK, at the same time, during the second week of the single. It was the first time that Westlife had held both the top album and the top single position in the same week and the first Irish music act to have such feat.<ref>{{cite news\n |url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/4413466.stm\n |title =Westlife celebrate chart double\n |work=BBC News|date =7 November 2005\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/60863/westlife-robbie-williams-top-uk-charts\n |title =Westlife, Robbie Williams Top UK Charts\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]]\n |first =Paul\n |last =Sexton\n |date =31 October 2005\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> This is their fifth No. 1 in the UK and sixth one in Ireland. \"You Raise Me Up\" was awarded as their fourth Record of the Year in the UK, for 2005. In December of that year, the group released \"[[When You Tell Me That You Love Me#Westlife version|When You Tell Me That You Love Me]]\", a duet with [[Diana Ross]], as the second single, and it debuted at its peak position of No. 2.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/60312/obscure-duo-nizlopi-tops-uk-singles-chart\n |title =Obscure Duo Nizlopi Tops UK Singles Chart\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] | first=Paul | last=Sexton\n |date=19 December 2005 | accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> This single marked its fourteenth year since the original Diana Ross version was released and peaked at No. 2, the same chart position in the UK Singles Chart in 1991. Westlife then released a third single, \"[[Amazing (Westlife song)|Amazing]]\", which debuted at No.&nbsp;4.<ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/59572/madonna-jack-johnson-take-lead-on-uk-charts\n |title =Madonna, Jack Johnson Take Lead on UK Charts\n |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] | first=Paul | last=Sexton\n |date=27 February 2006 | accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> After that, Westlife embarked on the \"[[Face to Face Tour]]\", travelling extensively to the UK, Ireland, [[Australia]] and Asia. This tour marked the first time that Westlife travelled to mainland [[China]] for a concert.<ref>{{cite web\n |url         = http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=114727\n |title       = China youth prefer Westlife to politics\n |publisher   = [[NineMSN]]\n |date        = 17 July 2006\n |accessdate  = 23 December 2007\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20120310013708/http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=114727\n |archivedate = 10 March 2012\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url =http://www.hmv.co.uk/hmvweb/displayProductDetails.do?ctx=12;5;34;61&sku=581342\n |title =Live at Wembley: Face To Face Tour 2006\n |publisher=[[HMV]]\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> The tour ranked the band sixth for the year with number of performances with 32 shows and recorded 238,718 paid-for attendances.<ref name=\"billboard.com\"/> A recording of a concert from the tour, live from Wembley Arena, was released in November 2006. The band was mentioned as part of the names of male groups that peaked in the United Kingdom album sales in 2005 with 45 percent of the market.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hitsdailydouble.com/news&id=311808|title=HITS Daily Double : Rumor Mill - SOLO MEN RULE U.K. MUSIC. WHY?|website=HITS Daily Double}}</ref> By this time, they already sold over 36 million records worldwide.\n\nIn late 2006, Westlife signed a brand new five-album deal with [[Sony BMG Music Entertainment]]. Their seventh album, ''[[The Love Album (Westlife album)|The Love Album]]'' was a compilation concept album which consisted of popular love-song covers. The album outsold other [[compilation album]]s by [[Oasis (band)|Oasis]], The Beatles, and [[U2 (band)|U2]] in its first week of release and went straight to No. 1 in both UK and Ireland. This is the top selling album of 2006 in Ireland and their seventh No. 1 album there. While the said album was their sixth No. 1 in the UK. The first single from ''The Love Album'', \"[[The Rose (Westlife song)|The Rose]]\", which became their 14th UK No.&nbsp;1 single.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/56683/westlife-jamiroquai-assume-control-of-uk-charts\n |title=Westlife, Jamiroquai Assume Control of UK Charts |publisher=[[Billboard charts]] |first=Paul |last=Sexton |date=13 November 2006 |accessdate=22 December 2007}}</ref> [[File:West life.jpg|thumb|200px|left|The band on their 2006 concert tour]] This made Westlife the third act (along with Cliff Richard) in the UK to have the most No.&nbsp;1 singles, tailing behind Elvis Presley <small>(21)</small> and The Beatles <small>(17)</small>. In Ireland, they made it to the second place (tied with The Beatles) to have most number one singles, tailing behind U2 <small>(21)</small>. They also returned to the Miss World stage where billions saw the exclusive live performance of The Rose. Westlife then kicked off their eighth world tour, \"[[The Love Tour]]\", in [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]], Australia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gm.tv/index.cfm?articleid=23776 |title=Love Westlife? |publisher=GMTV |accessdate=22 December 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071223042804/http://www.gm.tv/index.cfm?articleid=23776 |archivedate=23 December 2007  }}</ref> The group then went on to other Australian cities before moving on to South Africa, the UK and Ireland. The tour had a total of \u00a31,031,033 secondary gross sales.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.narip.com/news-46/|title=Curtains Up (or Down?) on the Concert Business |website=Narip.com}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 November 2007, Westlife released their eighth album, ''[[Back Home (Westlife album)|Back Home]]'', which contained nine new original songs along with three cover songs. The album debuted at No.&nbsp;1 on the UK, their seventh No. 1. This makes them as one of the only five band, with [[Coldplay]], [[The Prodigy]], [[Stereophonics]], and [[Take That]], in UK chart history to claim seven No. 1 albums. It was also 2007's fifth biggest selling album in the UK.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1047344/leona-lewis-westlife-lead-uk-charts | title=Leona Lewis, Westlife Lead UK Charts | publisher=[[Billboard charts]] |first=Paul |last=Sexton |date=12 November 2007 |accessdate=22 December 2007}}</ref> The album was their eighth No. 1 in Ireland. The first single released from the album was \"[[Home (Westlife song)|Home]]\", which peaked at No.&nbsp;3 in the UK.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/radio1/chart/singles.shtml\n |title=The UK Top 40 Singles |publisher=[[BBC Radio 1]]\n |accessdate=22 December 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stv.tv/content/out/music/display?id=opencms:/out/music/new_interviews/stv |title=Westlife: Pop's not dead! |publisher=[[STV (TV network)|STV]] |first=Euan |last=Wemyss |date=12 November 2007 |accessdate=22 December 2007 }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> \"[[I'm Already There]]\", not released as a single, managed to chart in the UK based on downloads alone, following a performance on an episode of ''The X Factor UK''.\n\nOn 15 December 2007, they had a two-hour show called ''[[The Westlife Show]]'' where they performed 10 of their songs, some of which were voted online by fans and some from ''Back Home''. It was hosted by [[Holly Willoughby]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvthrong.co.uk/music/the-westlife-show-live-saturday-15-december |title=The Westlife Show Live \u2013 Saturday 15 December |publisher=Tvthrong.co.uk |date=15 December 2007 |accessdate=13 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406081913/http://www.tvthrong.co.uk/music/the-westlife-show-live-saturday-15-december |archive-date=6 April 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Months later, \"[[Us Against the World (Westlife song)|Us Against the World]]\" was announced and released as their second single in UK and Ireland. Before the release of the second single, they embarked on the [[Back Home Tour]] on 25 February 2008. This tour marked the first time that the group had travelled and performed in [[New Zealand]], performing four sold-out shows in [[Auckland]], [[Wellington]], [[New Plymouth]] and [[Christchurch]]. Meanwhile, \"[[Something Right]]\" was released as the second single and \"Us Against the World\" became the third single in Europe and the Asia Pacific region. Both songs performed well on several music charts.\n\n===10th anniversary and hiatus (2008\u20132009)===\n[[File:WestlifeBackHomeTour.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Westlife performing at the [[Croke Park]] in 2008]]\nFrom 2005 to 2008, ''[[Music Week]]'' revealed on their website that Westlife was the official third top touring act within the years while they were the seventh top touring act of 2008.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cardew |first=Ben |url=http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=1&storycode=1038004&c=1 |title=Spice Girls top UK live league |work=Music Week |accessdate=13 October 2011}}</ref> On 28 March 2008, after 27 sell-out shows, in the space of 10 years and have sold 250,000 tickets. All four members were presented with a plaque cast of their hands, which can also be seen in the [[Wembley Arena Square of Fame|Wembley Square of Fame]] similar to [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanahotel.co.uk/concert-venues/wembley-arena|title=WEMBLEY ARENA \u2013 AMERICANA HOTEL LONDON UK \u2013 LAST MINUTE BOOKINGS \u2013 SPECIAL OFFERS \u2013 LONDON EVENTS \u2013 REGENTS PARK \u2013 DORSET SQUARE|website=americanahotel.co.uk}}</ref> Then to mark their tenth year in music, Westlife staged a special ''10 Years of Westlife'', a sold-out concert at the world's thirty-third biggest and Europe's fourth biggest stadium,<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.crokepark.ie/page/venue_information.html\n |title=Croke Park Stadium Venue Information\n |publisher=Croke Park Stadium\n |accessdate=15 January 2008\n |url-status=dead\n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071119040257/http://www.crokepark.ie/page/venue_information.html\n |archivedate=19 November 2007\n\n}}</ref> [[Croke Park]], on 1 June 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.westlife.com/news/2007/11/02/10_years_of_westlife_concert |title=10 Years of Westlife Concert |publisher=Westlife.com |accessdate=22 December 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071207235341/http://www.westlife.com/news/2007/11/02/10_years_of_westlife_concert |archive-date=7 December 2007 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> which Egan described to be a \"pop extravaganza\".<ref>{{cite news\n |url =http://www.metro.co.uk/fame/interviews/article.html?in_article_id=73492&in_page_id=11\n |title =60 SECONDS: Kian Egan\n |newspaper=Metro (Associated Metro Limited)\n |accessdate=31 March 2008}}</ref> It was only the second time for an Irish act to headline the stadium after [[U2]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.herald.ie/entertainment/music/cash-pile-of-34m-is-sweet-music-to-the-scripts-ears-and-thats-before-next-years-croker-date-30843266.html |title=Cash pile of \u20ac3.4m is sweet music to The Script's ears and that's before next year's Croker date |last=Deegan |first=Gordon |publisher=herald.ie}}</ref> Filan confirmed that a corresponding live concert DVD would be released. The group announced that they would be on hiatus for a year after their Back Home Tour<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.metroradioarena.co.uk/events/view.aspx?ev=1239&ef=1&kw=&st=1\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812070850/http://www.metroradioarena.co.uk/events/view.aspx?ev=1239&ef=1&kw=&st=1\n |url-status=dead\n |archive-date=12 August 2014\n |title=Westlife 'Back Home' Tour 2008\n |publisher=[[Metro Radio]]\n |accessdate=22 December 2007\n}}</ref> and that there would not be an album release in 2008 as they would be spending more time on the production of their tenth album.<ref name=ff1>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/music/interviews/Westlife-42732.html\n |title=Exclusive Westlife Mark Feehily Interview |publisher=Female First |first=Caz |last=Moss |accessdate=22 December 2007}}</ref> As promised, the group's official website confirmed on 27 September 2008 the release of a DVD on 24 November 2008 entitled ''[[Back Home Tour|10 Years of Westlife \u2013 Live at Croke Park Stadium]]'' which went straight to No.&nbsp;1 on UK, Ireland, South African, Hong Kong and New Zealand Music DVD charts.\nAs the group ended another successful tour, Walsh announced in the show ''[[Xpose]]'' that 1 July 2008 would be the official start of the longest hiatus of the group. He said that it will be a one-year break, from that day up to 1 July 2009. On 13 December 2008, while on a break, Westlife made an unexpected appearance during that year's ''X Factor'' final where they performed \"Flying Without Wings\" with runners-up [[JLS]]. After the performance, Filan and Byrne were interviewed on ''[[The Xtra Factor (UK TV series)|The Xtra Factor]]'' with Boyzone's Keating and [[Stephen Gately]]. As JLS also performed, \"I'm Already There\", Westlife's version of the song re-entered the UK Singles Chart at No.&nbsp;63 while a new entry on Ireland Singles Chart at No.&nbsp;47 due to extensive downloads only. In the last week of January 2009, a DVD entitled ''The Karaoke Collection'' was released. This is the first time [[Sony Music]] has released an official Karaoke disc for music videos in DVD format. In 27 February 2009 issue of ''[[The Herald (Ireland)|Herald Ireland]]'', Walsh revealed that Cowell had already picked three new songs which he believed would be instant hits. On 18 March 2009, Westlife won the Best Irish Pop Act on the [[2009 Meteor Awards]] for the ninth consecutive time.\n\n===''Where We Are'' and ''Gravity'' (2009\u20132010)===\nTheir tenth album, ''[[Where We Are]]'', was released on 30 November 2009 in the UK and peaked at No.&nbsp;2 on both Irish and UK Albums Charts. The lead single, \"[[What About Now (Westlife song)|What About Now]]\", was released a few weeks earlier on 23 October 2009, with digital downloads being available the day before. The said single peaked at No. 2 on both Irish and UK Singles Charts and ranked No. 85 in the year-end official sales chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uk-charts.top-source.info/top-100-2009.shtml|title=Top 100 2009 \u2013 UK Music Charts|website=uk-charts.top-source.info}}</ref> Following that month was the announcement of the ''Guinness Book of World Records'' for Westlife as the top selling album group of the 21st century with 10.74 million albums sold in the UK alone.\n\nThey were also part of the [[Haiti]] charity single in early 2010 with, \"[[Everybody Hurts]]\", which was organised by Cowell.<ref>{{cite news |last=Dyke |first=Peter |url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/view/118204/Simon-Cowell-to-record-charity-single-for-Haiti/ |title=Simon Cowell to record charity single for Haiti |work=Daily Star |date=21 January 2010 |accessdate=13 October 2011}}</ref> The said single peaked at No. 1 on both Irish and UK Singles Chart. The tour in support of this album was called, \"[[Where We Are#The Where We Are Tour|The Where We Are Tour]]\". The tour entered at number 50 of top concert tour for the third quarter of the year with 241,865 ticket sales.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pollstarpro.com/specialfeatures2010/2010ThirdQuarterYTDTicketSalesTop100Tours.pdf|title=Pollstar \u2013 Welcome to the New Pollstar!|website=pollstarpro.com|access-date=23 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119143640/http://www.pollstarpro.com/specialfeatures2010/2010ThirdQuarterYTDTicketSalesTop100Tours.pdf|archive-date=19 January 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> A recording of a concert from the tour, live from London, was released in November 2010. The eleventh album was recorded and processed with songwriter and producer [[John Shanks]] in London and [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]] and was entirely produced by Shanks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a280330/westlife-announce-new-album-release.html |title=Westlife announce new album release |work=Digital Spy |date=5 October 2010 |accessdate=13 October 2011}}</ref> On 14 November 2010, the single \"[[Safe (Westlife song)|Safe]]\" was released. It debuted on the UK Singles Chart on 21 November at No.&nbsp;10, giving the group their 25th Top 10 single in the United Kingdom. The new album titled ''[[Gravity (Westlife album)|Gravity]]'' was released on 22 November 2010.<ref>{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2010/09/30/westlife_new_album_announcement\n |title       = Westlife New Album Announcement\n |publisher   = Westlife.com\n |accessdate  = 30 September 2010\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20101009074543/http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2010/09/30/westlife_new_album_announcement\n |archivedate = 9 October 2010\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> It went to No.&nbsp;1 in Ireland and No.&nbsp;3 in the UK. This is their ninth No. 1 in Ireland and this album made Westlife as one of the few musical acts and band and the only pop band to have number one albums in three consecutive decades (1990s, 2000s, 2010s) in their home country.  \n[[File:Nobel Peace Price Concert 2009 Westlife2.jpg|thumb|260px|upright|Irish boy band Westlife performed at the [[Nobel Peace Price Concert]] in 2009.]]\nAs the [[2000s (decade)|2000s]] decade ends with 275 [[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 2000s|singles reached the No. 1 position on the chart in the UK]]. Over this period, Westlife were the most successful musical act and group at reaching the top spot with 11 No. 1 singles only from the said decade, top act with most total number of weeks at No. 1 with individual credits and second to most total number of weeks at No. 1 with 14 weeks. Ten out of their fourteen No. 1 singles were released and came from this decade. Westlife is also the second biggest selling music act in the UK of the 21st century. And second from the list of artist from the past decade, 1990s, in UK Albums and Singles Charts. While in 2005, half of the decade, they were the fifth.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/4413466.stm|title=Westlife celebrate chart double|date=7 November 2005|publisher=BBC}}</ref>\n\nWestlife was named the fourth most hard-working music artist and third most hard-working band in the UK by [[Performing Rights Society|PRS]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/2011/0108/andrep.html |title=Andre named 'hardest working singer' \u2013 RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann |accessdate=13 October 2011 |date=8 January 2011}}</ref> Also from the said year ''Billboard'' compiled the top international touring acts worldwide, the group ranked 14th with $5,104,109 estimated net take of tour grosses (assuming a typical 34% artist cut after commissions and expenses).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/?id=D0b70DQT1HkC&pg=RA5-PA20&lpg=RA5-PA20&dq=westlife+boxscore+billboard#v=onepage&q=westlife%20boxscore%20billboard&f=false|title=Billboard Jan 8 \u2013 Mar 26, 2011|date=8 January \u2013 26 March 2011}}</ref> In March 2011, they started their eleventh major concert tour, the [[Gravity Tour]]. This tour marked the first time the group travelled to [[Oman]], [[Namibia]], [[Guangzhou]] and [[Vietnam]] for concerts.\n\n===''Greatest Hits'', split (2011\u20132018)===\nAs of 2011, the group is the longest reigning band and second longest reigning number one music act in the 21st century in UK. On 14 March 2011, Westlife confirmed that they had left Cowell after 13 years and his record label [[Syco Music]] after nine years. The group cited Syco's decision not to release a second single from ''Gravity'' as the reason Byrne felt it as another reason of being unloved,\n\n{{quotation|We signed to Simon back in 1998 and he was brilliant, but then came the development of ''The X Factor'' and ''[[American Idol]]''. Simon became famous himself and his interests went that way rather than on Westlife. We almost felt a little bit unloved with Simon Cowell, if I was to be honest. We had it (full time support) with Simon but he got so busy and would do it at the very last minute and we needed someone who was on it all the time.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/westlife-felt-unloved-by-cowell_1212334 |title=Westlife Felt 'Unloved' By Cowell |magazine=Contactmusic |date=13 April 2011 |accessdate=13 October 2011}}</ref>}}\n\nOn 23 April 2011, Egan's [[Twitter]] account posted a series of tweets saying he was to walk away from the group. He later said his account was hacked and deny the announcement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/woman/celeb-news/westlifes-kian-falls-victim-to-twitter-hacker-26727336.html|title=Westlife's Kian falls victim to Twitter hacker|website=Independent.ie}}</ref> After going back to RCA Records full-time for a one-year album contract, they announced their ''[[Greatest Hits (Westlife album)|Greatest Hits]]'' album to be released on 21 November 2011. It debuted at No. 1 in Ireland and No. 4 in the UK. This is their tenth No. 1 album in Ireland. The first and lead single, \"[[Lighthouse (Westlife song)|Lighthouse]]\" was released in November 2011. And a follow-up promotional single \"[[Beautiful World (Westlife song)|Beautiful World]]\" released later. In October 2011, Egan ruled out speculation that McFadden would reunite with them for the new compilation album and its promotion for a television show. Egan said: \"All the rumours about Brian re-joining Westlife are untrue. We have been a 4 piece for too long now. We love Brian but it's not going to be. That includes any TV performances.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/egan-mcfaddens-not-rejoining-westlife_1251040 |title=Westlife &#124; Egan: 'Mcfadden's Not Rejoining Westlife' |magazine=Contactmusic |date=18 October 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2011}}</ref> With a new compilation album coming out, it was speculated Westlife would be doing a new greatest hits tour. They were scheduled to headline the [[ChildLine Concert]] in Dublin on 12 November 2011 and to have another exclusive concert on [[The O2 (Dublin)|O2]] Blueroom, also in Dublin on 24 November.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.o2online.ie/o2/the-o2/smart-sounds/?cm_sp=The-O2-_-Smart-Sounds-_-HP-Banner%201 |title=O2 Smart Sounds |publisher=O2online.ie |accessdate=13 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008151217/http://www.o2online.ie/o2/the-o2/smart-sounds/?cm_sp=The-O2-_-Smart-Sounds-_-HP-Banner%201 |archive-date=8 October 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stereoboard.com/content/view/167082/9 |title=The Wanted, Westlife And Jedward Confirmed For Dublin's Cheerios Childline Concert 2011 |website=Stereoboard |date=8 August 2011 |accessdate=13 October 2011}}</ref>\n\nA UK tour was first officially announced on 18 October 2011, with dates confirmed for May 2012 and it was titled, [[Greatest Hits Tour (Westlife)|The Greatest Hits Tour]] or The Farewell Tour. ''Stereoboard'' reported that the tour sold out within minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stereoboard.com/content/view/168422/9 |title=Westlife Tickets For May 2012 Farewell Tour Sell-Out After Hysterical Rush For Tickets |publisher=Stereoboard.com |date=21 October 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2011}}</ref> On 19 October 2011, Westlife officially announced they were splitting after an album and a tour.<ref name=rteten_split>[http://www.rte.ie/ten/2011/1019/westlife.html \"Westlife to split up\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111021042509/http://www.rte.ie/ten/2011/1019/westlife.html |date=21 October 2011 }}. ''RT\u00c9 Ten''. 19 October 2011.</ref>\n\n{{quotation|After 14 years, 26 top ten hits including 14 number one singles, 11 top 5 albums, 7 of which hit the top spot and have collectively sold over 44 million copies around the world, 10 sell out tours and countless memories that we will forever cherish, we today announce our plan to go our separate ways after a greatest hits collection this Christmas and a farewell tour next year. The decision is entirely amicable and after spending all of our adult life together so far, we want to have a well-earned break and look at new ventures. We see the greatest hits collection and the farewell tour as the perfect way to celebrate our incredible career along with our fans. We are really looking forward to getting out on the tour and seeing our fans one last time.\n\nOver the years, Westlife has become so much more to us than just a band. Westlife are a family. We would like to thank our fans who have been with us on this amazing journey and are part of our family too. We never imagined when we started out in 1998 that 14 years later we would still be recording, touring and having hits together. It has been a dream come true for all of us.\n\nKian, Mark, Nicky and Shane<ref>{{cite web|title=After 14 Years... |url=http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2011/10/19/after_14_years |accessdate=13 August 2012 |date=19 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106010153/http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2011/10/19/after_14_years |archivedate=6 November 2012 |df= }}</ref>}}\n\nDuring this time, the [[Official Charts Company]] compiled the band's chart history which states that other than their number-ones they had, 25 UK Top 10s, 26 UK Top 40s, 27 UK Top 75s, 20 Weeks at No. 1, 76 Weeks in Top 10, 189 Weeks in Top 40 and 282 Weeks in Top 75 in the [[UK Singles Chart]]. While 7 No. 1s, 12 UK Top 10s, Top 40s, Top 75s, 7 Weeks at No. 1, 92 Weeks in Top 10, 189 Weeks in Top 40, and 299 Weeks in Top 75 in the [[UK Albums Chart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/7712/westlife/ |title=Westlife |publisher=OCC |date=25 October 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2011 }}</ref> They also had seven number-one albums in eight years, the most number-ones with different albums by a music album act, group, pop group, and male group in UK Albums Chart in the 2000s and the second most number ones, tied with [[Rod Stewart]], with different albums by a music album act, group, pop group and male group in UK clustered per decade since The Beatles in the 1960s and of all time. In Ireland, they have fourteen No. 1 singles and ten No. 1 albums, the most for a pop band and act and male band and act, and Irish band next to U2.\n\nA second statement was issued through their official site, saying the fans were continuing to be the best support system.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2011/10/25/statement_from_westlife |title=Official News (GLOBAL) \u2013 Statement From |publisher=Westlife |date=25 October 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111027231010/http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2011/10/25/statement_from_westlife |archivedate=27 October 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Statement From Westlife |url=http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2011/10/25/statement_from_westlife |accessdate=13 August 2012 |date=25 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120501120111/http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2011/10/25/statement_from_westlife |archivedate=1 May 2012 |df= }}</ref> Some fans on social networks described themselves as feeling \"devastated\" following news of the split.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/article/313057 |title=Westlife announce that they are to split |publisher=Digitaljournal.com |accessdate=12 November 2011}}</ref><ref>[http://www.herald.ie/lifestyle/lifelong-fan-laura-butler-on-the-day-the-music-died-as-westlife-called-it-quits-2911766.html \"Lifelong fan Laura Butler on the day the music died as Westlife called it quits\"], herald.ie, 20 October 2011.</ref> People left their messages on Twitter by using #WestlifeForever and #Westlife, it trended on Ireland, [[Indonesia]], New Zealand, [[Philippines]], [[Singapore]], [[Sweden]], and UK. A live stream Q&A happened on 28 October 2011 as a \"thank you\" to their fans. As part of it, [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] commissioned a one-off music event as they took to the stage to sing some of their greatest hits, it was entitled ''Westlife: For the Last Time''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://steveandersonproductions.com/westlife-for-the-last-time-itv/|title=Westlife \u2013 For The Last Time (ITVl)|website=steveandersonproductions.com}}</ref> Another show entitled, ''[[The Westlife Show]]: Live'', was broadcast from [[The London Studios|Studio One]] of London Studios on the same channel on 1 November 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2011/10/23/the_westlife_show_live_itv1 |title=Official News (GLOBAL) \u2013 The Westlife Show: Live \u2013 ITV1 |publisher=Westlife |date=23 October 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111120061325/http://www.westlife.com/global/news/global/2011/10/23/the_westlife_show_live_itv1 |archivedate=20 November 2011}}</ref> They then had a live guesting on ''The Late Late Show''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/around-town/fans-in-shock-as-westlife-call-it-a-day-after-14-years-at-the-top-2911797.html |title=Fans in shock as Westlife call it a day after 14 years at the top |work=Herald.ie |accessdate=12 November 2011}}</ref> They were honored at that time by [[Scottish Exhibition and Conference Centre]] (SECC) with four specially commissioned bar stools to mark 49 performances at the venue for over 380,000 fans, selling more tickets than any other act.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/scottish-tribute-to-westlifes-signature-bar-stool-move-7869025.html|title=Scottish tribute to Westlife's signature bar stool move|date=20 June 2012|website=Evening Standard}}</ref> The band had their final concert on 23 June 2012 at Croke Park Stadium in Ireland. The 82,300 capacity show was sold out in 4 minutes. Due to this popular demand, an extra date was added at Croke Park on 22 June 2012, which also sold out. Combined, there was a total of 187,808 spectators on both nights, exceeding the capacity of the stadium.<ref name=\"music-news.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.music-news.com/shownews.asp?nItemID=45780 |title=Westlife sell out show in record breaking time and add date |publisher=Music-News.com |date=22 June 2012 |accessdate=15 August 2012}}</ref> Their last concert was also screened live in more than 300 cinemas in the United Kingdom,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livedesignonline.com/concerts/31-days-plots-iheartradio-alter-ego-2018 |title=XL Video supplies LED Screens for Westlife Farewell Concert |publisher=Livedesign |date=22 July 2012 |accessdate=15 August 2012}}</ref> and 200 cinemas worldwide.<ref name=\"westlifecinema.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.westlifecinema.com |title=WESTLIFE \u2013 THE FAREWELL CONCERT: Saturday, June 23rd |publisher=Westlifecinema.com |date=23 June 2012 |accessdate=15 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/worldwide/290512westlife|title=BBC \u2013 Westlife farewell to be screened live in cinemas across the UK, Ireland and mainland Europe \u2013 Media Centre|publisher=BBC}}</ref> They also released a DVD, which went to number 1 in both UK and Irish chart. In that year they were also declared the 34th top-grossing tour act of the year with earnings of $35.2&nbsp;million (\u20ac27&nbsp;million). The farewell tour consisted of eight dates in China and 33 in the UK and Ireland; in total, the band sold 489,694 tickets from the tour.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pollstarpro.com/files/011413top50.pdf|title=Pollstar \u2013 Welcome to the New Pollstar!|website=pollstarpro.com|access-date=19 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170514101637/https://www.pollstarpro.com/files/011413top50.pdf|archive-date=14 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nCowell and some media predicted a possible reunion in the future,<ref name=\"guardian1\">Jonze, Tim. [https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/oct/19/westlife-split-after-14-years?newsfeed=true \"Westlife to split after 14 years\"]. ''The Guardian'' (London). 19 October 2011.</ref> but Westlife put an end to that speculation by vowing they would never reunite.<ref>[http://www.rte.ie/ten/2011/1104/westlife.html \"Westlife rule out future comeback tour\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106201128/http://www.rte.ie/ten/2011/1104/westlife.html |date=6 November 2011 }}. Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann. 4 November 2011.</ref> Later reports from the ''[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]]'' said there was an \"irreparable rift\" in the band,<ref>[http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/showbiz/music-news/2011/10/20/westlife-blame-irreparable-rift-as-they-split-after-14-years-86908-23502249/ \"Westlife blame 'irreparable rift' as they split after 14 years\"], ''Daily Record'', 20 October 2011.</ref> but was later denied by a source close to the band saying: \"There's no bad blood in the band, they're still great pals. But all good things come to an end and they are all keen to do their own thing.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gulfnews.com/arts-entertainment/celebrity/westlife-it-s-over-1.916231 |title=Westlife: It's over |work=Gulf News |date=24 October 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2011}}</ref> Later, the band also denied it and called the split a \"united decision\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a347360/westlife-deny-band-rift-rumours-after-split-announcement.html |title=Westlife deny band rift rumours after split announcement |work=Digital Spy |date=25 October 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2011}}</ref> However he confessed three months after the split, Byrne said that members of the group fought with one another more and more often in the latter years leading up to the split and he felt that it was the right time to end their time together. A year after Westlife ended, they agreed to all voluntarily wind up Bluenet Ltd, their main entertainment firm, after going their own ways and split \u20ac2.3million to \u20ac595,500 each except for Filan who missed out any of it as he declared bankruptcy at that time due to property crash problems.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/showbiz/irish-showbiz/ruined-shane-misses-out-600000-2137517|title=Ruined Shane misses out on \u20ac600,000 pay day|first=Sam|last=Hamilton|date=8 August 2013|website=irishmirror}}</ref>\n\nSince the split, the four lads have released albums and singles individually. Filan, with three studio albums and with singles and tours (with support act dates for [[Lionel Richie]]) released and a Top 5 hit album in UK. Feehily associated with an independent record label (which he is the co-director) and released albums and singles. He also made it as a supporting act to Mariah Carey and [[Wet Wet Wet]]. Egan was voted King of the Jungle on the 2013 series of [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]'s ''[[I'm a Celebrity]]'' series, released one studio album with singles, was a coach judge on ''[[The Voice of Ireland]]'', and was a support act for Boyzone. Byrne released one studio album, joined ''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]'', hosted several major Irish television and radio shows, and represented Ireland in [[Eurovision]], which was also his debut solo single.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/westlife-now-mark-feehilys-catering-5034366|title=Westlife: Where are they now? From Mark's catering van to Shane's bankruptcy|first=Kara|last=O'Neill|date=24 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Syco Music said to ''[[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]'': \"All the guys are up for it in principle. It's now just a matter of sorting out all the details, Syco would love Brian to be part of the band again. It\u2019d create the same sort of buzz as when [[Robbie Williams]] returned to Take That. But the other lads will need to be convinced because they were always very clear that when Brian left it was for good.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/12/04/westlife-reunion-brian-mcfadden_n_6267206.html|title=Try To Remain Calm... Westlife Are Reforming!|date=4 December 2014}}</ref> but Egan later tweeted, \"Guys I'm sorry to say but I don't know where these rumours are coming from about a Westlife reunion but it's untrue. Sorry #westlifeforever.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2014/1204/664526-kian-egan-denies-westlife-reunion-rumours/|title=Kian Egan denies Westlife reunion rumours|date=4 December 2014}}</ref> In 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2015/0602/705295-louis-walsh-doesnt-rule-out-westlife-reunion/|title=Louis Walsh predicts Westlife comeback|date=2 June 2015}}</ref> 2016 (On this year, Walsh posted on the band's social accounts that they will not regroup as of the moment),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scoop.hollywood.com/breaking-news/louis-walsh-plotting-westlife-reunion-20168329/|title=Louis Walsh Plotting Westlife REUNION|date=11 August 2016}}</ref> 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.entertainmentdaily.co.uk/news/legendary-90s-boyband-set-to-reunite-but-one-member-will-be-missing/|title=Legendary 90s boyband set to reunite \u2013 but one member will be missing|date=13 December 2017}}</ref> Walsh expressed that the four-piece band would reunite. He had been in contact with [[Ed Sheeran]] and [[James Arthur]] to create songs for the band.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2017/1222/929284-louis-walsh-wants-ed-sheeran-to-write-for-westlife/|title=Louis Walsh wants Ed Sheeran to write for Westlife|date=22 December 2017|via=www.rte.ie}}</ref>\n\nHowever, on 2016\u20132017, four years following the split, Filan told ''[[Lorraine (TV programme)|Lorraine]]'' and other media outlets that while there are currently no plans for a Westlife reunion, he would not rule it out for the future.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/shane-filan-opens-up-westlife-8469388|title=Shane Filan opens up about Westlife reunion addresses X Factor rumours|first=Nicola|last=Agius|date=22 July 2016}}</ref> Byrne expressed in 2017, \"Shame this Westlife news is not true. They were always my guilty pleasures.\" He also talked about touring with the group: \"Who wouldn't want to do that again? The laugh with the boys and travelling around and seeing all the fans again. It's nearly six years next summer since we've done it so who knows? Maybe in ten years. I've spoken to all the lads individually but we've never brought up a Westlife reunion, the thing about it is the four of us haven\u2019t been in a room together since [[Jodi Albert|Jodi]]'s [Kian's wife] mum's funeral,' That was the last time we spoke properly as a band, if you want to call it that., I'm sure it will happen but I don't know when and I know know if even we know when the right time will be.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://evoke.ie/2017/11/17/showbiz/westlife-reunion-rumours|title=Nicky Byrne Addresses Westlife Reunion Rumours|date=17 November 2017}}</ref> Feehily added, \"People have offered us blank cheques to get back together but it's not about money. There are no plans to reform. The time isn't now. We all have a lot more that we want to achieve first. It feels way too soon to be honest, a 20th anniversary tour could still happen one day as 2019 is 20 years since we released our first single, while 2021 is 20 years since our first world tour. So you never know\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gulfnews.com/tabloid/music/westlife-reunion-not-happening-says-mark-feehily-1.2142806|title=Westlife reunion not happening, says Mark Feehily|last=IANS|date=18 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March 2018, it was reported on [[Allkpop]] that all of them might guest on a popular Korean musical show ''[[Immortal Songs 2]]'' but Filan was the only one who appeared on the show as a judge and a guest performer afterwards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2018/03/irish-pop-group-westlife-might-guest-on-immortal-song|title=Irish pop group Westlife might guest on 'Immortal Song'?|website=allkpop}}</ref> Egan answered that this and other reports were untrue and the rest of the group members sided with Egan's response after as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goss.ie/showbiz/westlife-respond-to-claims-that-simon-cowell-wanted-them-to-reunite-with-brian-mcfadden-154886|title=Westlife respond to claims that Simon Cowell wanted them to reunite with Brian McFadden|date=23 October 2018|website=Goss.ie}}</ref> Later they revealed they had been phoned up by Walsh and Cowell every six months since their split. On 23 September 2018, several Irish news outlets started reporting that the group has been signed to [[Universal Music Group]] for a new five-year album and tour deal with [[Virgin EMI Records]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goss.ie/featured/westlife-reunion-definitely-going-ahead-without-brian-mcfadden-152109|title=Westlife reunion 'definitely going ahead' \u2013 WITHOUT Brian McFadden \u2013 Goss.ie|date=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.her.ie/entertainment/heres-when-westlife-are-going-to-bring-their-reunion-tour-to-ireland-426907|title=Here's when Westlife are going to bring their reunion tour to Ireland|website=Her.ie}}</ref>\n\n===Reunion, new singles, tours, and ''Spectrum'' album (2018\u2013present)===\nOn 3 October 2018, the group formally announced that there'll be new music and a tour coming soon on their official social media accounts like on their newly created [[Instagram]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/westlife/|title=Westlife Official Instagram of Westlife.|publisher=Instagram}}</ref> Their reunion story caused huge fan reaction worldwide. According to the reports, they had been preparing for their comeback for the past year of 2017 as Feehily had said on the same year that he hoped to get them all together for a proper catch-up.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.herald.ie/news/westlife-star-mark-says-the-band-is-set-for-a-reunion-down-at-the-pub-36345597.html|title=Westlife star Mark says the band is set for a reunion... down at the pub|first=Melanie Finn-23 November 2017 02:30|last=AM|website=Herald.ie}}</ref> It was later revealed that Egan and Filan first talked about their reunion when [[Adele]] released \"[[Hello (Adele song)|Hello]]\" in late 2015.<ref name=\"Westlife\">{{cite web|url=http://www.1883magazine.com/music-features/music-features/westlife|title=Westlife|publisher=1883 Magazine|date=18 October 2018|accessdate=18 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181018122502/http://www.1883magazine.com/music-features/music-features/westlife|archive-date=18 October 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> While Byrne raised his concerns about \"...where Westlife's music fits into the current market\" and not wanting to be simply a \"nostalgia\" act.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/music/music-news/there-were-only-two-people-who-could-get-westlife-back-out-of-bed-in-2018-ed-sheeran-was-one-nicky-byrne-37450216.html|title='There were only two people who could get Westlife back out of bed in 2018 \u2013 Ed Sheeran was one' \u2013 Nicky Byrne|newspaper=Irish Independent|date=24 October 2018|accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref> He went on to say, \"While we were away, we realised what Westlife really meant to the fans \u2013 and to us.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.joe.ie/music/confirmed-westlife-officially-getting-back-together-going-tour-642953|title=CONFIRMED: Westlife are officially getting back together and going on tour|website=JOE.ie}}</ref> McFadden was not involved in the reformation as he said on an interview with ''[[Closer Magazine]]'', \"...there's no reason for me and the boys to stay buddies.\" and \"For me, it was just a job. I only met the guys when I joined the band and have no regrets about leaving.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/celebrity/brian-mcfadden-reason-keep-touch-westlife-bandmates-1166455.html|title=Brian McFadden has no reason to keep in touch with Westlife bandmates|website=Femalefirst.co.uk}}</ref> Their first live interviews and press conferences as a four-piece in six years were made 20 days later held in Dublin and Belfast where they revealed their plans to stick around longer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://2fm.rte.ie/2018/10/23/world-exclusive-westlife-first-interview-back-together/|title=WORLD EXCLUSIVE! WESTLIFE \u2013 FIRST INTERVIEW BACK TOGETHER|publisher=2fm.rte.ie}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rsvplive.ie/news/celebs/westlife-reveal-incredible-plans-more-13467714|title=Westlife reveal incredible plans for more concert dates as they insist they're 'not here to just do one show in Croke Park'|publisher=rsvplive.ie}}</ref> Days later, it was followed by several radio interviews in Manchester, [[Ulster]], Dublin and [[Glasgow]]. Walsh also said in separate interviews that the most important things now are the songs, it will be featured as an introduction to their new sound and added, \"I was just waiting for them to decide when. There were record deals on the table, but the icing on the cake was Ed Sheeran writing these amazing songs for them, as well as having Steve Mac, who produced their early songs, on track too.\" [...] \"Sheeran's input adds a contemporary edge\", \"I've heard the first two songs and they are just incredible.\"<ref name=\"Irish News\">{{cite news|url=https://www.irishnews.com/lifestyle/2018/11/19/news/louis-walsh-on-westlife-boyzone-the-x-factor-and-elf-on-the-shelf-1486894/|title=Louis Walsh on Westlife, Boyzone, The X Factor and Elf on the Shelf|newspaper=Irish News}}</ref> Mac and Sheeran have come up with four new tracks for them. One will be a single co-written by Sheeran. Some had been composed since 2016. The duo have co-written recent hits like the [[List of most streamed songs on Spotify|most streamed song on Spotify]], \"[[Shape of You]]\", and also \"[[Woman Like Me]]\" by [[Little Mix]], and \"[[Thursday (Jess Glynne song)|Thursday]]\" by [[Jess Glynne]]. Mac revealed the band's signature sound will be back.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://twitter.com/BANGShowbiz/status/1055802345718759430|title= Steve Mac: Westlife back with signature sound |work=Twitter|accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref> Feehily and Filan added, \"We\u2019re not trying to change Westlife's sound, we\u2019re trying to evolve\", \"We need to be a Westlife 2.0, a better version of ourselves. We wanted to come back and recreate Westlife's sound, but better, and be a better band, and the most important thing about any band is music.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://evoke.ie/2018/10/23/showbiz/gossip/ed-sheeran-wrote-westlife-songs|title=Ed Sheeran wrote Westlife songs two years BEFORE the band decided to reunite}}</ref> In November 2018, Byrne expressed 2019 will be \"one hell of a year\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/NickyByrne/status/1058455247218229253|title=@NickyByrne Another Planning meeting with these lads done.. 2019 is gonna be one hell of a year! |work=Twitter|accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref> On 19 December 2018, Egan and Feehily posted a picture of the group's first rehearsals together in six years and Egan added that \"2019 will be nothing but epic\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrkruItFHY3/|title=kianegan So this happened... our first sing song together since we got back together! 2019 will be nothing but Epic! Can't wait for you all to her the new tunes! All coming early 2019!!!! Graham Norton Jan 11 is where it all starts! #westlife #westlifetwenty|via=Instagram}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrkfJfzlkg7/|title=markusmoments Rehearsal time,bring on 2019! \u2764\ufe0f|via=Instagram}}</ref> A musical and a documentary film about them and their reunion were also reported.\n\n\"[[Hello My Love]]\",<ref name=\"Irish News\"/> their first single since 2011 was released on 10 January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BsV7G6vHL4j/|title=January 10th 2019 #HelloMyLove |publisher=Instagram}}</ref> It reached No. 1 in [[iTunes]] Store Top Songs in more than fifteen countries that include the United Kingdom and Ireland, reached top 10 in 23 countries, and charted in more than 50 countries only minutes after its release. It was released in four official versions: Original, instrumental, acoustic, and a remix. Their first UK, worldwide television and recorded professional appearance, performance in seven years and of the single was on ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'' on 11 January 2019 where it was tagged as \"one of the most highly-anticipated TV comebacks of the decade\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/a25570611/graham-norton-show-guests-x-men-american-horror-story-james-mcavoy-sarah-paulson/|title=The Graham Norton Show lines up an X-Men superhero and an American Horror Story star And Westlife, too. Obviously.|website=Digital Spy|date=13 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lovinmanchester.com/tv/the-first-graham-norton-of-2019-features-one-of-the-most-highly-anticipated-tv-comebacks-of-the-decade|title=The First Graham Norton of 2019 Features One of the Most Highly-Anticipated TV Comebacks of the Decade|publisher=lovinmanchester}}</ref> They also performed the single on the ''[[24th National Television Awards]]'' on 22 January 2019 and it was their first live television performance, first [[The O2 Arena]] and arena performance together in seven years. Their first Irish performance and television appearance together was in the finals night of ''[[Dancing With the Stars]] Ireland'' on 24 March 2019. Their first tour and first promotional tour in general and for a single release together outside UK and Ireland in seven years was on Singapore on 29 January 2019 to 1 February 2019.<ref name=\"Twitter\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/westlifemusic/status/1088224865100787713|title=Singapore! Excited for this\u2026 we'll see you next week \ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddec|publisher=Twitter}}</ref> It reached number-two in Ireland and Scotland. It was their highest charting on their official singles charts since the band's \"What About Now\" single in 2009, ten years ago.\n\nThe full-length album is released on 15 November 2019. It is in different formats like the CD, digital download, vinyl, and a limited box set edition. Some of the album formats are bundled with their official tour merchandise. It is their eleventh studio album, their first major album to be released in eight years and first studio album in nine years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/NickyByrne/status/1075178884885331968|title=Here we go again \ud83c\udfa4\ud83c\udfa4\ud83c\udfa4\ud83c\udfa4 Having just announced two Cardiff dates, that brings the Twenty Tour to 32 shows so far across Ireland & Uk, A brand new album coming after 8years in 2019! But.. it all kicks off on The Graham Norton Show on January 11th \ud83e\udd1e\ud83d\ude32@thgnshow @grahnort|publisher=Twitter}}</ref> In November 2018, the pre-order links for the upcoming album were released on [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] Australia,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com.au/TBC/dp/B07JJ3X6QD |title=TBC TBC (Artist) |publisher=Amazon Australia}}</ref> Japan,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/Westlife/dp/B07JJ3X6QD/ |title=TBC \u30a6\u30a8\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30d5  |publisher=Amazon Japan}}</ref> UK,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Westlife/dp/B07JJ3X6QD/ |title=Westlife \u2013 Westlife |publisher=Amazon UK}}</ref> and [[HMV]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://store.hmv.com/music/cd/title-tbc-(10) |title=Title TBC Westlife |publisher=HMV}}</ref> The album is titled ''[[Spectrum (Westlife album)|Spectrum]]''. The album peaked at number one in Ireland, Scotland, and the UK and was certified as Gold in the UK and as Platinum in Ireland. This is their first number one album in twelve years in the UK and in eight years in Ireland. This is also the fastest selling album in 2019 in Ireland. This is their eighth UK number-one album making them the fifth band (fourth until Coldplay got their eight number-one album week after) to have eight UK number-one albums with the likes of [[Led Zeppelin]], and [[R.E.M. (band)|R.E.M.]]. Overall, they are one of the only ten bands that has had eight number-one albums.<ref name=\"auto2\"/> It marks their eleventh number-one album in Ireland.\n\nTo promote the album before its release, more singles were released like the second one, also by Mac and Sheeran with [[Fred Again]] ([[George Ezra]], [[Prettymuch]], [[Rita Ora]]), which was called \"[[Better Man (Westlife song)|Better Man]]\". It was their second number one on the UK Singles Physical Chart and reached number two on the UK Singles Sales Chart and Scottish Singles Chart in 2019. It was also released in orchestral and acoustic versions. The third single, \"[[Dynamite (Westlife song)|Dynamite]]\", was released on 5 July 2019 and was released in three different mixes. The single was their 27th Top 10 hit in Scotland and 29th Top 40 hit in Ireland. The fourth single from the album, \"[[My Blood (Westlife song)|My Blood]]\", was released on 25 October 2019. \"My Blood\" ended up peaking at number ninety-six on the UK Singles Chart and at number-six on the [[Scottish Singles Chart]]. It also peaked at number forty-six in the Irish Singles Chart.\n\nSince their comeback in 2018, their previous singles \"What About Now\", \"World of Our Own\", \"Queen of My Heart\" and \"If I Let You Go\" reached the higher Gold certifications in the United Kingdom after ten, seventeen, eighteen, and twenty years of its releases respectively. \"Flying Without Wings\" was certified Platinum twenty years after its release. While \"The Rose\" after thirteen years, and \"Hello My Love\" after four months claimed its Silver certifications since its releases respectively in the same country. Six were certified in 2019, one in 2018.\n\nOn the evening of 17 October 2018, the UK and Ireland dates of their latest tour were announced through Westlife's social networks and was called [[The Twenty Tour]]. A pre-order site of the forthcoming new Westlife album, for both unsigned and limited signed (which was taken down minutes later), from their official store was cited where fans will receive an exclusive pre-sale code for early access tickets to the 2019 tour.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://shop.westlife.com/cart.html;jsessionid=2B4FEAE766F1C0A3CB57CD9A8D8CEF7F.t2 |title=Westlife Official Shop |publisher=shop.westlife.com}}</ref> Pre-sale tickets were all sold out before the general sale and the event had been described as a \"big one\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://planetradio.co.uk/cool-fm/local/gigs-nightlife/top-tips-to-increase-your-chances-of-getting-ed-sheeran-tickets/ |title=Top Ticketmaster tips to increase your chances of getting Westlife tickets |publisher=planetradio.co.uk|date=24 October 2018 }}</ref> making the original tour dates sold out at the very time of its general sales opening. The tour had twelve original dates and fourteen more dates added on places like [[Liverpool]], [[Leeds]], and Sheffield in less than seven hours due to high demand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mcd.ie/westlife-add-2nd-croke-park-show-due-phenomenal-demand/|title=WESTLIFE ADD 2ND CROKE PARK SHOW DUE TO PHENOMENAL DEMAND!|date=18 October 2018|accessdate=18 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/104728-westlife-add-dates-to-the-twenty-tour-get-your-tickets/ |title=Westlife add dates to The Twenty Tour, get your tickets|publisher=list.co.uk|date=25 October 2018|accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/entertainment/music/music-news/westlife-announce-20th-anniversary-tour-13434350?1 |title=Westlife tickets go on sale with extra Glasgow dates added to meet huge demand for boyband's 20th anniversary tour|newspaper=Daily Record|date=25 October 2018|accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/westlife-announce-extra-uk-tour-13479386 |title=Westlife announce extra UK tour dates for 2019 comeback shows|work=The Mirror|date=25 October 2018|accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://evoke.ie/2018/10/25/showbiz/westlife-come-back-tour |title=Westlife tickets sell out in less than SIX minutes for comeback tour |publisher=evoke.ie|date=25 October 2018 }}</ref> In their first full print interview as a band in six years, they said: \"We will get to everyone eventually.\" Egan added, \"Every country that wants to see Westlife will see us at some point. We won't step away from this until we've managed to tour the world.\"<ref name=\"Westlife\"/> Seventeen additional Asian dates were announced from 21 March 2019 onwards; the tour has a total of fifty-one dates and took place at some of Asia's and Europe's largest indoor arenas and stadium. It was their fastest selling tour to date.\n\nThe second day of the tour in Croke Park had a live film broadcast in selected cinemas in at least fourteen European countries on 6 July 2019, and in more than 600 cinemas live via satellite in UK and Ireland alone. A delayed broadcast in at least nine Asian countries that include Hong Kong, India, [[UAE]], [[Bahrain]], [[Qatar]], and in Australia and New Zealand were done from August 2019 as well. They hired the [[Cirque du Soleil]] team for the production, stage design, and routines of the tour. A follow-up cinema screenings of the filmed tour date was produced from August 2019 onwards as well in a sing-along version that kick-started in Denmark, Ireland, and UK. This will be released in a video album in different formats on 13 March 2020.\n\nIn 13 September 2019, they announced that they are scheduled to play at [[Wembley Stadium]] in London on 22 August 2020 and at [[P\u00e1irc U\u00ed Chaoimh]] in [[Cork (city)|Cork]], Ireland on 28 and 29 August 2020, both for the first time, as part of their [[Stadiums in the Summer Tour]].\n\n==Popularity==\nWestlife's debut album and single coincided with the apogee of boy band popularity, and their success was most apparent in Ireland, the UK, and most of [[Africa]]n, Asian, Australian and European continental countries. They had album certifications in [[Brazil]], Mexico, and the United States as well. They had 13 worldwide concert tours and sold over 5.5&nbsp;million tickets. On April 2001, over one million fans wanted to chat with the lads from 122 countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://globenewswire.com/news-release/2001/04/26/280883/16386/en/Over-One-Million-Westlife-Fans-from-122-Countries-Wanted-to-Chat-with-the-Band-at-fanglobe-com-Prior-to-Their-Concert-in-Stockholm.html |title=Over One Million Westlife Fans from 122 Countries Wanted to Chat with the Band |publisher=GlobalNewsWire}}</ref> Voted worldwide as the best boy band on ''[[MTV|MTV Battle of the Boybands]]'' with thirty-two bands in the choices in 2012. Their battle between Backstreet Boys garnered the highest rate of votes with more than one million in a specific voting time only. The total votes throughout the two-week competition got more than 12 million votes. The final battle was between them and the [[Jonas Brothers]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1684589/westlife-win-mtvs-battle-of-the-boy-bands/|title=WESTLIFE WIN MTV'S BATTLE OF THE BOY BANDS|date=7 May 2012|publisher=MTV}}</ref> They have more than 50,000 official fans club members in mainland China alone in 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=114727 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20060718132744/http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=114727 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2006-07-18 |title=China youth prefer Westlife to politics |publisher=MSN}}</ref> Also in China's largest music streaming site, [[QQ Music]], they are the most followed western boy band, third western band, fourth male band, and twenty-fifth overall international music act as of August 2019. Boy band [[One Direction]] was mistaken for Westlife in [[Ghana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/celebrity-news/374613/One-Direction-mistaken-for-Westlife-in-Africa|title=One Direction mistaken for Westlife in Africa|date=31 January 2013}}</ref> They are the biggest selling international, foreign album act in Indonesian and [[Philippine]] music records history. They are the only international artist who is able to sell an album with more than one million units in Indonesia and their ''Westlife'' and ''Coast to Coast'' albums are in the top ten best selling albums of all-time in the Philippines. They are [[Vietnam]]'s most viewed music artist in YouTube as of 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-33022160|title=YouTube tool reveals music secrets|first=Mark|last=Savage|date=5 June 2015|publisher=BBC}}</ref> Their version of \"You Raise Me Up\" is on the top 75 best selling singles of all time in Australia. Voted by the public four times as [[The Record of the Year]] and twice as Best Pop Act on Brit Awards in the UK where they also have the most awards and nominations on the said category's history. In 2000s, \"Swear It Again\" became a popular song for wedding and funerals in the [[British Isles]]. In 2009, \"Flying Without Wings\" was listed as seventh most popular song for wedding's first dances in UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/5927826/Lonestars-Amazed-voted-most-popular-song-for-wedding-first-dances.html|title=Lonestar's Amazed voted most popular song for wedding first dances|date=29 July 2009|work=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref> In 2012, their version of \"You Raise Me Up\" and also \"Flying Without Wings\" made it to the top 20 most popular songs used at funerals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/londonnewsdesk/view/59732/|title=Songs by Westlife and Robbie Williams used most at funerals|date=15 October 2012|work=pressparty}}</ref> In 2016, three of their songs (\"[[Where We Are|I'll See You Again]]\", \"Flying Without Wings\", \"You Raise Me Up\") made it on the top pop music choices for funerals in Ireland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.98fm.com/uncategorized/westlife-music-revealed-as-popular-choise-for-funerals-168918|title=Westlife Revealed as Popular Music Choice for Funerals|website=98fm.com}}</ref> In 2019, \"You Raise Me Up\" appeared as the eighth top pop music choices in funerals in the United Kingdom and second in [[Northern Ireland]]. In [[South Korea]], their albums ''Coast to Coast'' and ''World of Our Own'' are the top two best selling albums from a western boy band of all time and nine out of twenty albums listed in the top best-selling albums of western boy bands of all time are from the band. Also in South Korea, their singles \"My Love\" and \"You Raise Me Up\" stayed in the top 75 of the [[Gaon chart|Official International Karaoke Charts]] since the inception of the charts in December 2010 up to its recent chart released.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/karaoke.gaon?termGbn=month&hitYear=2018&targetTime=05&nationGbn=E |title=Official International Karaoke Charts |publisher=Gaon}}</ref> The only Irish act, pop band, boy band to have two of previous [[Marvel Entertainment|Marvel]] [[Hollywood]] Actors had been cast in two of the lads' music videos. [[Vinnie Jones]] who played as Juggernaut in ''[[X-Men: The Last Stand]]'' was featured as the Duke Vincent in \"Bop Bop Baby\", while [[Ioan Gruffudd]] who played as [[Mr. Fantastic]] in ''[[Fantastic Four]]'' 2005 and 2007 was featured as one of the high class customers in \"Uptown Girl\". The only Irish act, pop band, boy band to have worked with three ''American Idol'' judges (Mariah Carey, Simon Cowell, Lionel Richie). Demo song \"[[Beautiful in White]]\" reached more than 242 million views (on a single video only) on YouTube as of November 2019, making it as the most successful original song from a pop act that was not released as an official single and never made any albums (until Filan released a different version for his solo album, accompanied with an official music video).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XRuDQ6aYeD0 |title=Westlife \u2013 Beautiful in White |work=YouTube}}</ref> Their song \"My Love\" is the most viewed, liked, and shared [[Facebook]] video post from a boy band and their medley video is also the second most liked one.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/1017520618305990/videos/1671925199532192/ |title=My Love |work=Facebook}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/makingmemoriesofficials/videos/1503714906347573/ |title=Making Memories |work=Facebook}}</ref>\n\nThey were invited by [[Wayne Rooney]] and [[Coleen Rooney]] to sing on their wedding reception in [[Portofino]], [[Abbey of Cervara]], [[Italy]] and got paid \u00a3400,000, one of the highest amount paid acts, highest for a pop band, boy band and Irish act and band for a wedding in world history. They are Coleen's favorite pop band, also invited to her 21st birthday but was unable to make it. Egan said later that it was more of Rooney who is a big fan of the band as revealed to them by Coleen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/uk/entertainment/news/a3219/coleen-loves-westlife-82499/|title=Coleen loves Westlife|date=28 May 2008}}</ref> The band also performed for the [[Sultan of Brunei]], an occasion on which they were paid \u00a32.5&nbsp;million to play a private concert of seven songs.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/shane-filan-dyed-hair-tan-4392310 |title=Westlife \u2013 Shane Filan talks about getting paid \u00a3500,000 |work=Daily Mirror |location=London |date=6 October 2014 |accessdate=17 October 2014}}</ref> They also performed at the [[Nobel Peace Prize Concert]] in 2000 with \"I Lay My Love on You\" and \"My Love\", in 2005 with the songs \"World of Our Own\" and \"You Raise Me Up\" with [[Rolf L\u00f8vland]] and [[Fionnuala Sherry]], and in 2009 with \"What About Now\" and \"You Raise Me Up\" in front of former US President [[Barack Obama]] and met him afterwards.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ipUzLjzjrvk|title=Westlife and Secret Garden \u2013 You Raise Me Up (Nobel Peace Price Concert 2005) HD|last=pommivabrik|date=15 March 2010|via=YouTube}}</ref> They also played for [[Queen Elizabeth II]] twice and for [[Pope John Paul II]] once in a live concert television show and shook hands with them after.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/queen-elizabeth-II/8525207/The-Queen-watches-Riverdance-Westlife-and-The-Chieftains-at-Irish-music-concert.html|title=The Queen watches Riverdance, Westlife and The Chieftains at Irish music concert|first=BST 20 May|last=2011|date=20 May 2011}}</ref> They were the first ever pop band to top the entertainment bill at the [[Vatican City]] and a private concert for the Pope.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ticketmaster.co.uk/Westlife-tickets/artist/711587 |title=Westlife \u2013 Biography |publisher=Ticketmaster.co.uk}}</ref> They also personally met former [[UK Prime Minister]] [[Tony Blair]] and picked autographs also for his daughter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1180918.stm|title=PM gets Westlife autographs|date=20 February 2001|publisher=BBC}}</ref> The band was also mentioned in the book version of ''[[Me Before You]]'', which was released in 2012. Westlife's songs were also used as film soundtracks six times that include \"Safe\" for ''[[Dolphin Tale]]'' in 2011, \"You Raise Me Up\" for ''[[Mrs. Brown's Boys D'Movie]]'' in 2014 and \"Flying Without Wings\" for ''Pokemon: The Movie 2000''. Their songs were also used as soundtracks for television shows such as ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]'', ''[[Coronation Street]]'', ''[[Dancing on Ice]]'', ''[[Emmerdale]]'', ''[[EastEnders]]'', ''[[So You Think You Can Dance]] UK'', and ''The X Factor UK'' (they are the most performed professional and international live music act in ''X Factor'' as well). Westlife's name was used by the main character Vicky Pollard in the popular UK comedy television series ''[[Little Britain]]'' with one of her famous lines, \"swapping her baby for a Westlife CD\". They were referenced as part of  [[1990s]] pop culture on the British band [[Busted (band)|Busted]]'s 2018 music video \"[[Nineties (song)|Nineties]]\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=James Bourne |title= @JamesBourne Wondering if Westlife will retaliate now with a music video wearing school uniforms jumping around in the playground with guitars |url=https://twitter.com/JamesBourne/status/1061968292993216512 |website=Twitter |accessdate=17 November 2018 |date=12 November 2018}}</ref> Their songs appeared in more than a thousand compilation albums.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/152450-Westlife?filter_anv=0&type=Appearances|title=Westlife discography|date=20 February 2001|publisher=Discogs}}</ref>\n\nDespite their success worldwide, Westlife was unable to break into the U.S. market. They had only one hit single in the United States, \"Swear It Again\", which peaked at No. 20 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 in 2000. The band made an appearance on MTV's ''[[Total Request Live]]'' and the U.S. edition of their debut album, ''Westlife'' was released, but it didn't meet with success. In 2002, with the two most prominent boy bands in the US, the Backstreet Boys and [[*NSYNC]], going on hiatus that year, an attempt was made to promote and release a US version of \"World of Our Own\", but was never successful. ''Billboard'' called the failure due to corporate politics.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://books.google.com/?id=BQwEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA21&lpg=PA21&dq=billboard+westlife+corporate+politics#v=onepage&q=billboard%20westlife%20corporate%20politics&f=false |title=Reviews and Previews \u2013 Spotlight \u2013 Westlife \u2013 World of Our Own |magazine=Billboard|date=10 August 2002 }}</ref>\n\n{{Quote|\"We sent over a CD of ''World of Our Own'' with no name on it. They didn't know it was Westlife and every single radio station in the States \u2013 all came back and said that this is an absolutely huge hit. They said it was great for radio and people are gonna love it, especially as there's just a slight bit of rock guitar to it. But as soon as we revealed it was Westlife, the radio pluggers all went, 'Whoa, not Westlife \u2013 it's a boyband.' And we cannot break that down, no matter what song we come out with. The problem with America is that it's all radio and you've got to break into radio first. And currently radio doesn't want to play boy bands or pop music. If [[Bono]] wrote a song with us tomorrow and it was the biggest hit in the world, if Westlife's name is put to it, it won't be a hit in America because radio will not play us.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news-article/westlife-.blacklisted.-in-america |title=Westlife 'Blacklisted' In America|work=Contactmusic.com |date=8 July 2003 |accessdate=15 August 2012}}</ref>|Nicky Byrne, 8 July 2003 interview}}\n\n\"Flying Without Wings\" peaked at number-two in the US when ''American Idol: Season 2'' winner [[Ruben Studdard]] recorded and released it as his debut single. In 2003, Westlife went to [[Nashville]] to film a TV documentary. While they were there, they gave a live performance of the song \"[[Daytime Friends]]\", originally by country music singer [[Kenny Rogers]]. Though Westlife didn't gain as much success in the States as they did elsewhere, their music was still appreciated. Kid David Corey, assistant PD and music director at top 40 WXKS (Kiss 108) radio station in [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]] was a Westlife supporter that was recorded saying \"Bands like Backstreet Boys and 'N Sync are still climbing the charts, and radio is supporting them, so I don't think the boy band thing is going to hurt them. Besides, this song [\"Swear it Again\"] is just too good for any of that to be a concern. I can't imagine anyone not playing this because it's another boy band, especially when it doesn't even sound like those other guys.\"<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Taylor|first1=Chuck|title=Dublin's darling Westlife wins over Europe, aims for success in U.S.|journal=ProQuest|date=5 February 2000|volume=112|issue=6|page=110|id={{ProQuest|1011343}}}}</ref>\n\nCelebrities including [[Elton John]], [[Sharon Osbourne]], [[Chris Martin]] of Coldplay, [[Jamie Vardy]], [[Mike Tyson]], [[Martine McCutcheon]], [[Niall Horan]], [[BoybandPH#Neil Murillo|Neil Murillo]], [[Leona Lewis]], [[C. J. Stander]], [[Daniel Bedingfield]], [[Ed Sheeran]], [[Rebecca Ryan]], [[John Newman (singer)|John Newman]], [[Emily Atack]], [[Calvin Harris]], [[Sam Mangubat]], [[Stormzy]], [[Greg O'Shea (rugby union)|Greg O'Shea]], [[Sofie Hagen]], [[Gemma Collins]], [[Matt Kilgallon]], [[Shona McGarty]], [[Alexandra Burke]], [[Harry Styles]], [[Michael Devlin (footballer)|Michael Devlin]], [[Scott McKenna]], [[Ed Drewett]], [[Dominic Ball]], [[Dan Osborne]], [[Union J]], James Arthur, [[Zhong Chenle]] and [[Robert Pattinson]] have recognized their love for Westlife's music.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.stv.tv/music/275416-westlife-confirm-split-after-final-glasgow-gig/  |title=Westlife confirm split after final Glasgow gig |publisher=Entertainment.stv.tv |date=19 October 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oneindia.com/2008/05/30/chris-martin-dreams-favourite-band-westlife-1212147240.html|title=Chris Martin 'dreams' about favourite band Westlife|date=30 May 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://popdust.com/2012/11/27/one-direction-westlife-robert-pattinson-twilight-interview/ |title=Robert Pattinson: The Lone English Bloke Who Doesn't Know a One Direction Song |publisher=Popdust.com | date=27 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://popdirt.com/elton-john-backs-westlife-over-oasis-in-album-chart-race/54814/|title=Elton John Backs Westlife Over Oasis in Album Chart Race |website=popdirt.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/niallofficial/status/24911387599835136|title=@ellaappleyard I'm a westlife and take that fan|first=Niall|last=Horan}}{{Primary source inline|date=July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/DannyO/status/1045427842501234689 |title=@DannyO Retweeted sammy \u2665 \ud83d\ude02 Omg there's a reunion???? @westlifemusic please tell me this is true!! |first=Daniel|last=Osborne}}{{Primary source inline|date=September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/UnionJworld/status/1017488366261145601 |title=@dannyb234 Robbie Williams and Westlife #UnionJAliveMidnight JJx |first=Union|last=J}}{{Primary source inline|date=July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/160268880731612/posts/ed-sheeran-just-mentioned-westlife/336974776394354/|title=Ed Sheeran just mentioned Westlife in his speech on itunes festival! He told the crowd to put their arm around the person next to them and sway as if you were listening to Westlife|first=WestlifeCrew|last=WestlifeCrew}}{{Primary source inline|date=July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/AberdeenFC/status/1022445928685420544 |title=AberdeenFC |publisher=Twitter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailyedge.ie/westlife-calvin-harris-song-similarity-1839772-Dec2014/ |title=Is the new Calvin Harris song weirdly similar to an old Westlife song? |publisher=dailyedge.ie |date=19 October 2014 |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.penguin.co.uk/articles/in-conversation/interviews/2016/oct/10-things-you-might-not-know-about-jamie-vardy/ |title=In conversation \u2013 10 things you might not know about Leicester City player Jamie Vardy |publisher=Penguin UK |date=19 October 2016 |accessdate=12 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713080817/https://www.penguin.co.uk/articles/in-conversation/interviews/2016/oct/10-things-you-might-not-know-about-jamie-vardy/ |archive-date=13 July 2018 |url-status=dead  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://sportplaylists.com/player-playlists-bradford-city-defender-matt-kilgallon |title=Player Playlists: Bradford City defender Matt Kilgallon |publisher=Sport Playlist |date=19 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/playlist/guest-playlist-nct/pl.70049bc6566347fc9fc09a5aa4767487 |title=Guest Playlist: NCT |publisher=Apple Music |date=19 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://metro.co.uk/2017/11/14/eastenders-star-shona-mcgarty-reveals-lee-ryans-reaction-when-she-told-him-she-preferred-westlife-to-blue-7078706/ |title=EastEnders star Shona McGarty reveals Lee Ryan's reaction when she told him she preferred Westlife to Blue |work=Metro|location=UK |date=19 October 2017 |accessdate=12 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.ie/woman/celeb-news/westlife-scale-new-heights-with-double-celebration-25923848.html |title=Westlife scale new heights with double celebration |work=The Irish Independent |date=19 October 2003 |accessdate=12 November 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2003/mar/22/artsfeatures.popandrock |title=Daniel Bedingfield |work=The Guardian |date=19 October 2003 |accessdate=12 November 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.irishmirror.ie/whats-on/whats-on-news/gemmacollins-living-with-lucy-kennedy-13221241 |title=Lucy Kennedy to cosy up with TV star Gemma Collins on 'Living with Lucy' |date=10 September 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lfjN2FKLml8 |title=Leona Lewis meets Westlife on X-Factor.wmv |publisher=YouTube |date=12 February 2019 |accessdate=12 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2015/dec/13/sofie-hagen-comedy-standup-review-soho-theatre-london |title=Sofie Hagen review \u2013 comical confessions of a Westlife obsessive |newspaper=The Guardian |date=13 December 2015 |last1=Logan |first1=Brian }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://timthoughtsblog.wordpress.com/2017/03/08/amazing-facts-you-may-want-to-know-about-sam-mangubat-2/ |title=AMAZING FACTS YOU MAY WANT TO KNOW ABOUT SAM MANGUBAT |date=8 March 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/news/155231-boybandph-facts-pinoy-boyband-superstar-winners|title=BoybandPH: 6 things to know about the 'Pinoy Boyband Superstar' winners|first=Alexa|last=Villano|website=Rappler}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/JamesArthur23/status/1040567763683692545 |title=James Arthur23 |publisher=Twitter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/RebeccaRyan1/status/1088144305628372994 |title=RebeccaRyan1 |publisher=Twitter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/EmAtack/status/1088044809946828800 |title=EmAtack |publisher=Twitter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Harry_Styles/status/108887173889142785 |title=Had on 4music 'every number on if the naughties' before.. Westlife-Unbreakable. I must admit... I air-grabbed. |publisher=Twitter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/VodafoneIreland/status/1094174063998758913 |title=\ud83d\ude2eYou won't believe who @CJStander has recently started listening to! |publisher=Twitter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/westlife/news/westlife-to-unite-with-mike-tyson|title=westlife to unite with mike tyson? |website=mtv.co.uk}}</ref> Some well-known music artists like Ronan Keating, [[Will Young]], [[Shayne Ward]] and Ruben Studdard have also covered their songs. Some of the following are original songs by Westlife that have been covered by other artists (which includes professionally recorded or performed list only). Some were officially released as a single.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"|width=100%\n|-\n! style=\"width:250px;\"|Song\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Covered By\n|- \n|Ai Yi Tian Duo Yi Tian (Open Your Heart)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/best-of-daniel-chan-mw0001253515|title=Best of Daniel Chan \u2013 Daniel Chan